id,specification,constraints,config,resource_type,num_constraints
0,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name model-trainer-pod, deployed to ml. Specifications include bearing the label team=backend, built from kibana:11, with a memory request of 4Gi.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4Gi""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: model-trainer-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: model-trainer
    team: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: kibana:11
    ports:
    - containerPort: 3306
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 4Gi
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,6
1,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name metrics-collector-ingress, deployed to staging. Specifications include responding to requests for shop.example.com, and with a Prefix pathType.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""shop.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-ingress
  namespace: staging
spec:
  rules:
  - host: shop.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /graphql
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,5
2,Set up an Ingress called cache-proxy-ingress in the development namespace. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have directing traffic for the host blog.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blog.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-ingress
  namespace: development
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: blog.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: payment-gateway-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - blog.example.com
    secretName: cache-proxy-tls",Ingress,4
3,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name user-service, deployed to platform. Specifications include with its container called main, employing RollingUpdate for deployments, having 5 replicated pods, and pulling centos:latest.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: user-service
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: user-service
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: user-service
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: user-service
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: centos:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: APP_NAME
          value: '3'",Deployment,7
4,The rate-limiter-cron CronJob operates in the staging namespace. It has naming the container runner. It has executing on the */15 * * * * cron schedule. It includes requesting 100m CPU. It includes OnFailure restart behavior.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/15 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100m""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: '*/15 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: python:3.1
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 100m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure",CronJob,7
5,"Please configure a CronJob identified as cron-runner-cron within platform. Make sure it has the container labeled worker, triggered by cron expression 0 12 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 12 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-cron
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    team: ml
spec:
  schedule: 0 12 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: minio/minio:2.0
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '1'
                memory: 1Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  suspend: false",CronJob,5
6,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name user-service, deployed to development. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. Specifications include with 6 replicas, built from python:alpine, with its container called app, while also with API_KEY configured as false.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: user-service
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: user-service
    tier: database
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: user-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: user-service
        tier: database
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: python:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8500
        env:
        - name: API_KEY
          value: 'false'",Deployment,7
7,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name queue-worker-cron, deployed to monitoring. Specifications include running on schedule 0 6 * * *, tagged as app=stream-consumer, preserving the last 5 successful runs, preserving the last 3 failed runs.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: queue-worker-cron
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
spec:
  schedule: 0 6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: logstash:17
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,7
8,"We need a ConfigMap named health-checker-config in data. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. The configuration requires containing the cache_ttl entry, where the debug_mode entry includes tru.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""tru""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: health-checker-config
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: testing
data:
  retry_count: '10'
  cache_ttl: '300'
  debug_mode: 'true'",ConfigMap,5
9,"Please configure a Service identified as data-pipeline-svc within production. Make sure it has communicating over TCP, and also forwarding to target port 9090, forwarding traffic to pods with app=config-server, exposing port 3000, configured as NodePort.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-svc
  namespace: production
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: config-server
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
10,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name event-bus-ingress, deployed to default. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. Specifications include using the event-bus-tls TLS secret, with a Exact pathType, routing to backend service service-mesh-svc, and responding to requests for staging.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-tls""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: event-bus-ingress
  namespace: default
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /admin
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: service-mesh-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - staging.example.com
    secretName: event-bus-tls",Ingress,7
11,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name ssl-terminator, deployed to monitoring. Specifications include using bitnami/kafka:stable as its container image, and also with its container called main, scaled to 3 instances.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: staging
    team: infra
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: ssl-terminator
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: ssl-terminator
        env: staging
        team: infra
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: bitnami/kafka:stable
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,6
12,The auth-service Deployment operates in the data namespace. It has whose container is called worker. It features pulling memcached:3.1. It is configured with env var TIMEOUT assigned to false. It includes accepting connections on container port 6379. It has a replica count of 1.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""memcached:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: auth-service
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: auth-service
    team: platform
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: auth-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: auth-service
        team: platform
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: memcached:3.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: 'false'",Deployment,8
13,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name cron-runner, deployed to staging. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Specifications include with a replica count of 1, with the container labeled worker, running rabbitmq:latest, and capping CPU at 100m.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cron-runner
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cron-runner
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cron-runner
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: rabbitmq:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,7
14,The service-mesh Deployment operates in the default namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It has having 5 replicated pods. It requires built from nats:17. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It includes running in a container named app.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:17""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: service-mesh
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: service-mesh
    team: platform
    tier: backend
    version: v1.0
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: service-mesh
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: service-mesh
        team: platform
        tier: backend
        version: v1.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: nats:17
        ports:
        - containerPort: 15672
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 64Mi
        env:
        - name: DATABASE_URL
          value: production",Deployment,6
15,"We need a Service named inventory-svc-svc in ml. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. The configuration requires targeting port 5432, and as a LoadBalancer service.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: user-service
  ports:
  - port: 5432
    targetPort: 5432
    protocol: TCP",Service,5
16,The ssl-terminator-svc Service operates in the default namespace. It requires ClientIP session affinity. It has of type ClusterIP. It is configured with forwarding traffic to pods with app=audit-logger.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-svc
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    tier: queue
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: audit-logger
  ports:
  - port: 3306
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,6
17,Configure an Ingress called inventory-svc-ingress in the infra namespace. It should have responding to requests for blog.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blog.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-ingress
  namespace: infra
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: 'true'
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: blog.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: notification-svc-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - blog.example.com
    secretName: inventory-svc-tls",Ingress,4
18,"We need a Deployment named stream-consumer in platform. The configuration requires naming the container worker, using Never image pull policy, with TIMEOUT configured as 8080, additionally built from golang:3.0, and with a replica count of 10.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    env: testing
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: stream-consumer
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: stream-consumer
        env: testing
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: golang:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: '8080'",Deployment,8
19,We need a CronJob named inventory-svc-cron in default. The configuration requires triggered by cron expression 30 2 * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-cron
  namespace: default
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: alpine:1.0
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,4
20,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name image-processor, deployed to data. Specifications include with the container labeled image-processor, while also built from node:stable, while also environment variable NODE_ENV=60, running 3 copies, and with container port 9000.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""60""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: image-processor
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: image-processor
    env: testing
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: image-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: image-processor
        env: testing
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: image-processor
        image: node:stable
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 512Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: NODE_ENV
          value: '60'",Deployment,8
21,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name pdf-generator-config, deployed to monitoring. Specifications include mapping app_port to 9090, where redis_host contains red.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""red""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: pdf-generator-config
  namespace: monitoring
data:
  app_name: notification-svc
  app_port: '9090'
  debug_mode: 'true'
  retry_count: '3'
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0",ConfigMap,5
22,"Spin up a Deployment called session-store in the platform namespace. It should have Never image pull policy, pulling envoyproxy/envoy:latest, with 1 replicas, and with its container called app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: session-store
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: session-store
    tier: database
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: session-store
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: session-store
        tier: database
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 256Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: DATABASE_URL
          value: '3'",Deployment,7
23,"Set up a Deployment called queue-worker in the ml namespace. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. It should have maintaining 8 pods, with its container called worker, and with ruby:alpine as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ruby:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: queue-worker
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
    team: platform
    env: production
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: queue-worker
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: queue-worker
        team: platform
        env: production
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: ruby:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        env:
        - name: DEBUG
          value: 'false'",Deployment,6
24,"Please configure a CronJob identified as user-service-cron within platform. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Make sure it has handling concurrent runs via Forbid, running on schedule 0 0 1 * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 1 * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Forbid""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: user-service-cron
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    team: backend
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 1 * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: memcached:3.9
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,5
25,"Deploy a ConfigMap called queue-worker-config in the default namespace. It should have app_name containing the text ord, and with database_url containing the text mys.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""mys""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""ord""}]","apiVersion: v1
