47,"Please configure an Ingress identified as load-balancer-ingress within data. Make sure it has handling traffic for app.example.com, and also with path matching set to ImplementationSpecific.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ImplementationSpecific""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-ingress
  namespace: data
  annotations:
    proxy-body-size: 50m
  labels:
    env: staging
spec:
  rules:
  - host: app.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: service-mesh-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - app.example.com
    secretName: load-balancer-tls
  ingressClassName: traefik",Ingress,5
48,The cron-runner-ingress Ingress operates in the infra namespace. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It has a Prefix pathType. It requires routed through the nginx ingress class. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. It requires responding to requests for docs.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""docs.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-ingress
  namespace: infra
spec:
  rules:
  - host: docs.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: ml-inference-svc
            port:
              number: 80
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,6
49,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name health-checker, deployed to production. Specifications include running 5 copies, based on the kibana:stable image, and also with a CPU request of 2, and whose container is called worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
