77,"Provision a Deployment called report-gen in the ml namespace. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. It should have a replica count of 10, with the container labeled worker, pulling logstash:3.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: report-gen
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: report-gen
    release: stable
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: report-gen
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: report-gen
        release: stable
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: logstash:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8500
        env:
        - name: REDIS_URL
          value: '3'",Deployment,6
78,The log-aggregator-ingress Ingress operates in the default namespace. It has bound to host v2.api.example.com. It requires carrying annotation ssl-redirect: /. It requires pathType Exact. It has routing to backend service webhook-relay-svc.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""log-aggregator-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.ssl-redirect"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-svc""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: log-aggregator-ingress
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: /
  labels:
    env: staging
spec:
  rules:
  - host: v2.api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: webhook-relay-svc
            port:
              number: 5000",Ingress,7
79,"We need a Deployment named ssl-terminator in staging. The configuration requires pulling nats:latest, with its container called ssl-terminator, with 2 replicas, and where PORT equals production.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    version: v2
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: ssl-terminator
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: ssl-terminator
        version: v2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: ssl-terminator
        image: nats:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 1Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 64Mi
        env:
        - name: PORT
          value: production",Deployment,7
80,The ml-inference-config ConfigMap operates in the data namespace. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It is configured with max_connections configured as 10. It requires a api_key_prefix entry present. It features where the debug_mode entry includes tru.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""tru""}, {""path"": ""data.api_key_prefix"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-config
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: staging
data:
  api_key_prefix: pk-
  max_connections: '10'
  debug_mode: 'true'
  allowed_origins: '*'",ConfigMap,6
81,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name cron-runner-pod, deployed to data. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Specifications include running node:8.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:8""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-pod
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
    tier: database
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: node:8
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9000
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 1000m
        memory: 2Gi",Pod,4
82,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name ssl-terminator-pod, deployed to development. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. Specifications include with busybox:21 as the base image, reserving 750m CPU resources, running in a container named runner, additionally authenticated as service account monitoring-sa, labeled env=production.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:21""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""750m""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring-sa""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: busybox:21
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 750m
        memory: 64Mi
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,8
83,Please configure a CronJob identified as cdn-origin-cron within production. Make sure it has executing on the 0 */6 * * * cron schedule.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 */6 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin-cron
  namespace: production
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  schedule: 0 */6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: alpine:4.0
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,4
84,"Create a Deployment called stream-consumer in the default namespace. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. It should have a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, with the container labeled worker, pulling nats:5.0, having 4 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    team: backend
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: stream-consumer
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: stream-consumer
        team: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: nats:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432",Deployment,7
85,"We need a Pod named web-app-pod in infra. The configuration requires consul:16 as the base image, while also using restart policy Never, naming the container server, bearing the app label web-app, and with port 15672 open.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: web-app-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: web-app
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
