    - containerPort: 15672
  serviceAccountName: default",Pod,8
86,"We need an Ingress named web-app-ingress in monitoring. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. The configuration requires a Exact pathType, directing traffic for the host example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: web-app-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
  annotations:
    description: Ingress for web-app-ingress
  labels:
    env: production
spec:
  rules:
  - host: example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: user-service-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - example.com
    secretName: web-app-tls
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,5
87,"Create a Service called config-server-svc in the monitoring namespace. It should have service type ClusterIP, and targeting pods with app=ml-inference.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
