            cpu: 100m
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi",Deployment,6
162,"We need a CronJob named frontend-cron in default. The configuration requires the team label set to backend, allocated 500m CPU, with the cron schedule 0 0 1 * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 1 * *""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500m""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: frontend-cron
  namespace: default
  labels:
    team: backend
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 1 * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: redis:21
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 500m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid",CronJob,6
163,"We need a ConfigMap named dns-resolver-config in data. The configuration requires where the app_port entry includes 808, while also having the workers field, where the app_port field is 8080, with workers configured as 4, and where the log_level entry includes err.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""808""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""err""}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver-config
  namespace: data
data:
  workers: '4'
  app_port: '8080'
  log_level: error
  api_key_prefix: sk-",ConfigMap,8
164,"Create a Pod called api-server-pod in the default namespace. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. It should have a memory request of 128Mi, and also with Never restart behavior, with port 8443 open, additionally setting DATABASE_URL to info, and pulling elasticsearch:3.9.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""128Mi""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8443""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""info""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: api-server-pod
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: api-server
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: elasticsearch:3.9
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8443
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 500m
        memory: 128Mi
    env:
    - name: DATABASE_URL
      value: info",Pod,8
165,Set up an Ingress called rate-limiter-ingress in the data namespace. It should have directing traffic for the host cdn.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-ingress
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: cdn.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: catalog-api-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - cdn.example.com
    secretName: rate-limiter-tls",Ingress,4
166,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name data-pipeline-pod, deployed to staging. Specifications include with httpd:4.0 as the base image, whose container is called app, and with imagePullPolicy set to IfNotPresent.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""IfNotPresent""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: httpd:4.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 27017
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
  serviceAccountName: admin",Pod,6
167,"Configure a Deployment called cdn-origin in the development namespace. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. It should have a CPU request of 500m, with container port 8443, the container identified as worker, additionally having 4 replicated pods, and also using mongo:8 as its container image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8443""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cdn-origin
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cdn-origin
        release: canary
    spec:
