182,"Deploy a ConfigMap called frontend-config in the data namespace. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. It should have feature_flags configured as dark_mode=false, with redis_host configured as redis://cache:6379/0, and also containing the redis_host entry, and where the redis_host entry includes red.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dark_mode=false""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis://cache:6379/0""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""red""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: frontend-config
  namespace: data
data:
  cache_ttl: '60'
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false",ConfigMap,7
183,"Please configure a Deployment identified as batch-processor within production. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Make sure it has the DATABASE_URL environment variable, and also running logstash:21, additionally with 10 replicas, running in a container named app, requesting 750m CPU.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""750m""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""DATABASE_URL""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: batch-processor
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: batch-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: batch-processor
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: logstash:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 4Gi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: DATABASE_URL
          value: '8080'",Deployment,8
184,"Deploy a CronJob called queue-worker-cron in the platform namespace. It should have whose container is called job, and also restart mode set to OnFailure, with the cron schedule 0 */6 * * *, and running memcached:1.2.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 */6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""job""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""memcached:1.2""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: queue-worker-cron
  namespace: platform
spec:
  schedule: 0 */6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: memcached:1.2
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 250m
                memory: 4Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure",CronJob,7
185,Set up an Ingress called user-service-ingress in the default namespace. It should have responding to requests for admin.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: user-service-ingress
  namespace: default
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: proxy-server-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,4
186,"Configure a CronJob called data-pipeline-cron in the development namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. It should have executing on the 0 0 1 * * cron schedule, restart mode set to Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 1 * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-cron
  namespace: development
  labels:
    team: backend
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 1 * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: node:21
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,5
187,"Deploy a Deployment called api-server in the development namespace. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. It should have traefik:21 as the base image, maintaining 8 pods, whose container is called app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""traefik:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: api-server
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: api-server
    tier: queue
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: api-server
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: api-server
        tier: queue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: traefik:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 1Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: production",Deployment,6
188,The order-service-pod Pod operates in the development namespace. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It includes pulling grafana/grafana:21.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana/grafana:21""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: order-service-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: order-service
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: grafana/grafana:21
    env:
    - name: APP_NAME
      value: debug
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,4
189,The image-processor-pod Pod operates in the staging namespace. It is configured with ruby:stable as its container image. It features accessible via port 8443. It includes carrying the app=image-processor label. It features pulling images with policy Never.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ruby:stable""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8443""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: image-processor-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: image-processor
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: ruby:stable
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8443
    env:
    - name: METRICS_PORT
      value: production
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,7
190,"Please configure a Deployment identified as web-app within monitoring. Make sure it has running in a container named server, using alpine:21 as its container image, with a replica count of 8.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-app
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: web-app
    release: canary
    version: v3.0
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web-app
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web-app
        release: canary
        version: v3.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: alpine:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 256Mi
          limits:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: JWT_SECRET
          value: '8080'",Deployment,6
191,"Deploy a Pod called order-service-pod in the development namespace. It should have needing 256Mi memory, while also including APP_NAME in its environment, with minio/minio:slim as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""APP_NAME""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""256Mi""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: order-service-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: order-service
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: minio/minio:slim
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9090
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 256Mi
    env:
    - name: APP_NAME
      value: 'false'
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,6
192,We need a ConfigMap named frontend-config in production. The configuration requires where rate_limit contains 100.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""100""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: frontend-config
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: health-checker
data:
  rate_limit: '1000'
  log_level: debug
  cache_ttl: '600'
  debug_mode: 'false'
  allowed_origins: https://app.example.com",ConfigMap,4
193,The cdn-origin-ingress Ingress operates in the infra namespace. It requires routing requests to admin.example.com. It features TLS termination using secret cdn-origin-tls. It features ingressClassName set to haproxy.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-tls""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""haproxy""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin-ingress
  namespace: infra
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v2
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: health-checker-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - admin.example.com
    secretName: cdn-origin-tls
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,6
194,"Spin up a Deployment called audit-logger in the platform namespace. It should have serving on container port 15672, having 3 replicated pods, naming the container audit-logger, while also declaring the TIMEOUT env var, built from busybox:3.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TIMEOUT""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: audit-logger
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: audit-logger
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: audit-logger
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: audit-logger
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: audit-logger
        image: busybox:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 15672
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 256Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: info",Deployment,8
195,Set up a CronJob called proxy-server-cron in the staging namespace. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have triggered by cron expression 0 3 * * 1-5.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 3 * * 1-5""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: 0 3 * * 1-5
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: rabbitmq:20
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '1'
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,4
196,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name email-sender-cron, deployed to production. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. Specifications include running on schedule 0 0 * * *, while also whose container is called task, and using restart policy Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: email-sender-cron
  namespace: production
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: vault:1.0
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,6
197,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name image-processor-cron, deployed to monitoring. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. Specifications include preserving the last 1 failed runs, restarting on Never, with the container labeled task, running on schedule */30 * * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: image-processor-cron
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: vault:3.0
          restartPolicy: Never
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,7
198,The report-gen-cron CronJob operates in the staging namespace. It is configured with running a command starting with python. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. It includes handling concurrent runs via Forbid. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. It has triggered by cron expression */10 * * * *. It is configured with the container identified as runner. It requires needing 2 of CPU.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/10 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Forbid""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: report-gen-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: '*/10 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: busybox:2.0
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '2'
                memory: 512Mi
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid",CronJob,8
199,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name circuit-breaker-config, deployed to data. Specifications include containing app_name set to search-engine, and mapping app_env to development.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker-config
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: development
data:
  log_level: info
  app_env: development
  retry_count: '10'
  timeout_seconds: '60'
  allowed_origins: '*'
  app_name: search-engine",ConfigMap,5
200,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name web-app-ingress, deployed to monitoring. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Specifications include bound to host admin.example.com, backed by service load-balancer-svc, with port 8080 open, and matching /docs.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/docs""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: web-app-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: load-balancer-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  ingressClassName: traefik",Ingress,7
201,"Set up a Deployment called log-aggregator in the infra namespace. It should have a replica count of 6, with the container labeled main, and running traefik:4.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""log-aggregator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""traefik:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: log-aggregator
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: log-aggregator
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: log-aggregator
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: log-aggregator
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: traefik:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: '60'",Deployment,6
202,"We need a Service named auth-service-svc in logging. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. The configuration requires matching pods carrying app=stream-consumer, annotated with team=infra, additionally listening on port 8080, with service type LoadBalancer, via UDP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: auth-service-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: auth-service
    team: infra
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: stream-consumer
  ports:
  - port: 8080
    targetPort: 27017
    protocol: UDP",Service,8
203,The image-processor-pod Pod operates in the production namespace. It requires nats:alpine as the base image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:alpine""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: image-processor-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: image-processor
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: nats:alpine
    env:
    - name: DATABASE_URL
      value: 'true'
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: admin",Pod,4
204,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name report-gen-pod, deployed to platform. Specifications include built from httpd:8.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:8""}]","apiVersion: v1
