metadata:
  name: report-gen-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: report-gen
    team: infra
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: httpd:8",Pod,4
205,We need a Pod named notification-svc-pod in infra. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. The configuration requires pulling nats:1.0.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:1.0""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: notification-svc
    tier: cache
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: nats:1.0
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
    env:
    - name: METRICS_PORT
      value: debug
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Pod,4
206,The cache-proxy-svc Service operates in the monitoring namespace. It features communicating over UDP. It includes service type NodePort.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
    tier: frontend
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: image-processor
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9000
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 30919",Service,5
207,The proxy-server-pod Pod operates in the production namespace. It features built from busybox:16. It includes its container called worker. It has the CACHE_TTL environment variable. It includes the app label set to proxy-server.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CACHE_TTL""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: proxy-server
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: busybox:16
