  timeout_seconds: '5'
  rate_limit: '1000'
  redis_host: redis://redis:6379",ConfigMap,3
217,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name gateway, deployed to ml. Specifications include having 4 replicated pods, built from memcached:latest, and also requesting 1 CPU, allocated 256Mi memory, with the container labeled gateway.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""memcached:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""256Mi""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: gateway
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: gateway
    tier: database
    team: data
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: gateway
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: gateway
        tier: database
        team: data
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: gateway
        image: memcached:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: REDIS_URL
          value: 'true'",Deployment,8
218,The audit-logger Deployment operates in the staging namespace. It has built from consul:16. It features labeled tier=queue. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. It is configured with having 8 replicated pods. It has naming the container audit-logger. It requires exposing container port 3000.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: audit-logger
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: audit-logger
    tier: queue
    team: infra
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: audit-logger
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: audit-logger
        tier: queue
        team: infra
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: audit-logger
        image: consul:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        env:
        - name: WORKERS
          value: '8080'",Deployment,8
219,Set up a CronJob called model-trainer-cron in the monitoring namespace. It should have set to fire at */10 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/10 * * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
