  app_port: '8080'
  retry_count: '10'
  max_connections: '50'
  app_env: staging
  debug_mode: 'true'",ConfigMap,6
241,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name user-service-cron, deployed to development. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. Specifications include using nats:16 as its container image, with OnFailure restart behavior, and set to fire at */15 * * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/15 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:16""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: user-service-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: '*/15 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: nats:16
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - cleanup.sh
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 50m
                memory: 4Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5",CronJob,6
242,"Please configure a Deployment identified as ml-inference within logging. Make sure it has serving on container port 80, while also with the container labeled main, using elasticsearch:21 as its container image, scaled to 1 instances.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""80""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: ml-inference
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: ml-inference
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: ml-inference
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: ml-inference
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: elasticsearch:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 512Mi
        env:
        - name: DATABASE_URL
          value: production",Deployment,7
243,"Create a Pod called dns-resolver-pod in the ml namespace. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. It should have built from debian:5.0, additionally having WORKERS set to 8080, additionally exposing port 9090, while also using restart policy Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: debian:5.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9090
    env:
    - name: WORKERS
      value: '8080'
  serviceAccountName: default",Pod,7
244,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name catalog-api-pod, deployed to data. Specifications include with port 8500 open, additionally using envoyproxy/envoy:1.1 as its container image, running under service account admin, running in a container named worker, additionally bearing the app label catalog-api.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8500""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
