261,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name stream-consumer-cron, deployed to production. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Specifications include needing 1 of CPU, while also scheduled at 30 2 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer-cron
  namespace: production
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: elasticsearch:3.0
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '1'
                memory: 128Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Replace
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,5
262,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name inventory-svc-pod, deployed to default. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. Specifications include with TIMEOUT configured as true, labeled app=inventory-svc, and also running debian:slim, and restarting on Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:slim""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""true""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-pod
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
    tier: queue
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: debian:slim
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: 'true'",Pod,7
263,The webhook-relay-pod Pod operates in the development namespace. It has postgres:8 as its container image. It features a restart policy of Always.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
