277,"Please configure an Ingress identified as scheduler-ingress within default. Make sure it has accessible via port 3000, carrying label env: development, bound to host cdn.example.com, and with path matching set to Exact.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: scheduler-ingress
  namespace: default
  labels:
    env: development
spec:
  rules:
  - host: cdn.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /health
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: report-gen-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,7
278,"Set up a Pod called metrics-collector-pod in the data namespace. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. It should have running alpine:stable, and reserving 1000m CPU resources.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000m""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-pod
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    env: development
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: alpine:stable
    ports:
    - containerPort: 11211
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 1000m
        memory: 256Mi
    env:
    - name: MAX_RETRIES
      value: 'false'",Pod,5
279,The search-engine Deployment operates in the staging namespace. It has a RollingUpdate rollout strategy. It requires running openjdk:21. It includes NODE_ENV configured as 8080. It has its container called server. It is configured with having 6 replicated pods.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: search-engine
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: search-engine
    tier: cache
    version: v3.0
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: search-engine
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: search-engine
        tier: cache
        version: v3.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: openjdk:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
        env:
        - name: NODE_ENV
          value: '8080'",Deployment,8
280,"Please configure a CronJob identified as scheduler-cron within production. Make sure it has concurrency policy Replace, executing on the */5 * * * * cron schedule, which is not suspended, pulling consul:2.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Replace""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.suspend"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""False""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: scheduler-cron
  namespace: production
  labels:
    team: data
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: consul:2.0
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Replace
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5",CronJob,7
281,Set up a ConfigMap called auth-service-config in the staging namespace.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}]","apiVersion: v1
