    app: analytics-engine
  ports:
  - port: 8200
    targetPort: 8200
    protocol: TCP",Service,5
294,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name worker-svc, deployed to data. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Specifications include matching pods carrying app=notification-svc, communicating over TCP, configured as LoadBalancer, and also serving on port 9092, and forwarding to target port 6379.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9092""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: worker-svc
  namespace: data
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: notification-svc
  ports:
  - port: 9092
    targetPort: 6379
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
295,"Configure a CronJob called backend-cron in the infra namespace. It should have running on schedule 0 0 * * *, keeping 2 failed job(s) in history, the container identified as task.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: backend-cron
  namespace: infra
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: node:21
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 750m
                memory: 1Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,6
296,The inventory-svc-ingress Ingress operates in the logging namespace. It is configured with a Exact pathType. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It features directing traffic for the host app.example.com. It has accessible via port 3000.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-ingress
  namespace: logging
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: /
  labels:
    app: scheduler
spec:
  rules:
  - host: app.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: session-store-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,6
297,The gateway-ingress Ingress operates in the development namespace. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. It is configured with responding to requests for api.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: gateway-ingress
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
spec:
  rules:
  - host: api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: metrics-collector-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,4
298,Configure a CronJob called ml-inference-cron in the default namespace. It should have triggered by cron expression */5 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-cron
  namespace: default
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: nginx:3.1
          restartPolicy: Never",CronJob,4
299,"Please configure a CronJob identified as notification-svc-cron within development. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Make sure it has its command starting with /bin/sh, based on the golang:4.0 image, and scheduled at 30 2 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:4.0""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-cron
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: gateway
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: golang:4.0
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
          restartPolicy: OnFailure",CronJob,6
300,The gateway-pod Pod operates in the default namespace. It features ruby:14 as the base image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ruby:14""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: gateway-pod
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: gateway
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: ruby:14",Pod,4
301,"We need a Service named event-bus-svc in logging. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The configuration requires proxying to port 8080 on the backend, as a ClusterIP service, additionally bearing the label tier=queue, additionally serving on port 443, and also routing to pods where app is stream-consumer.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: event-bus-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: event-bus
    tier: queue
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: stream-consumer
  ports:
  - port: 443
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: UDP",Service,8
302,"We need a Deployment named worker in development. The configuration requires scaled to 6 instances, and also running elasticsearch:16, running in a container named app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
