  name: payment-gateway-svc
  namespace: data
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: order-service
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,6
354,The email-sender-svc Service operates in the platform namespace. It features matching pods carrying app=ssl-terminator. It includes port 9000 open. It requires configured as NodePort. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. It requires operating on UDP.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: email-sender-svc
  namespace: platform
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: ssl-terminator
  ports:
  - port: 9000
    targetPort: 8443
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
355,The health-checker Deployment operates in the monitoring namespace. It features pulling kibana:8. It requires running in a container named worker. It has running 8 copies.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: health-checker
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: health-checker
    team: backend
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: health-checker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: health-checker
        team: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: kibana:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 1Gi",Deployment,6
356,The gateway Deployment operates in the data namespace. It has a replica count of 8. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. It is configured with container port 3000. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It features its container called app. It features pulling ubuntu:17.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:17""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: gateway
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: gateway
    env: staging
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: gateway
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: gateway
        env: staging
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: ubuntu:17
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000",Deployment,7
357,The ml-inference-pod Pod operates in the ml namespace. It requires where JWT_SECRET equals production. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It requires python:1.1 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: ml-inference
    tier: frontend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: python:1.1
    env:
    - name: JWT_SECRET
      value: production
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,5
358,The catalog-api-svc Service operates in the default namespace. It has via TCP. It has configured as ClusterIP. It is configured with configured with ClientIP affinity.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: catalog-api-svc
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: catalog-api
    team: data
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: api-server
  ports:
  - port: 5432
    targetPort: 80
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,6
359,"Create a CronJob called stream-consumer-cron in the ml namespace. It should have in an active (unsuspended) state, triggered by cron expression 0 0 * * 1, labeled env=staging, and also using Allow concurrency, built from postgres:stable.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 1""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.suspend"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""False""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Allow""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer-cron
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    env: staging
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 1
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: postgres:stable
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 250m
                memory: 1Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  suspend: false
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,8
360,"Please configure a Deployment identified as inventory-svc within staging. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Make sure it has RollingUpdate as the strategy type, additionally having 8 replicated pods, and also using envoyproxy/envoy:16 as its container image, additionally annotated with release=blue, and whose container is called worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.release"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blue""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
    release: blue
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: inventory-svc
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: inventory-svc
        release: blue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        env:
        - name: WORKERS
          value: '8080'",Deployment,8
361,"We need a ConfigMap named ssl-terminator-config in logging. The configuration requires where the database_url entry includes mon, while also with app_name containing the text gat, having database_url=mongodb://mongo:27017/app in its data, and with a api_key_prefix entry present.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""data.api_key_prefix"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongodb://mongo:27017/app""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""gat""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""mon""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-config
  namespace: logging
data:
  retry_count: '3'
  api_key_prefix: api-
  rate_limit: '5000'
  database_url: mongodb://mongo:27017/app
  app_name: gateway",ConfigMap,7
362,We need a ConfigMap named webhook-relay-config in logging. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-config
  namespace: logging
data:
  app_name: backend
  app_port: '8080'
  app_env: staging
  log_level: info
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false",ConfigMap,3
363,"We need an Ingress named report-gen-ingress in platform. The configuration requires TLS enabled for host docs.example.com, listening on port 8080, and also handling traffic for docs.example.com, directing traffic to service analytics-engine-svc, using pathType Prefix.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""docs.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""docs.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""analytics-engine-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: report-gen-ingress
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: session-store
spec:
  rules:
  - host: docs.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: analytics-engine-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - docs.example.com
    secretName: report-gen-tls",Ingress,8
364,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name order-service-cron, deployed to logging. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Specifications include configured with Allow concurrency handling, carrying label team: backend, scheduled at */30 * * * *, preserving the last 1 successful runs, and naming the container runner.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Allow""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: order-service-cron
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    team: backend
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: golang:17
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,8
365,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name feature-store-ingress, deployed to staging. Specifications include responding to requests for grafana.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: feature-store-ingress
  namespace: staging
  annotations:
    proxy-body-size: 50m
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
spec:
  rules:
  - host: grafana.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,4
366,"We need a ConfigMap named report-gen-config in platform. The configuration requires storing log_level with value debug, additionally mapping app_env to staging, storing feature_flags with value enable_v2=true, including a allowed_origins data key, where feature_flags contains ena.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""enable_v2=true""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""ena""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: report-gen-config
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    team: ml
data:
  allowed_origins: '*'
  log_level: debug
  feature_flags: enable_v2=true
  max_connections: '200'
  app_env: staging",ConfigMap,8
367,"Create a Service called email-sender-svc in the production namespace. It should have TCP protocol, proxying to port 6379 on the backend, annotated with tier=frontend, and also of type ClusterIP, serving on port 9000.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: email-sender-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: email-sender
    tier: frontend
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: image-processor
  ports:
  - port: 9000
    targetPort: 6379
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
368,"We need a Deployment named health-checker in development. The configuration requires allocated 1Gi memory, having 5 replicated pods, needing 750m of CPU, with the container labeled app, and also built from golang:4.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1Gi""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""750m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: health-checker
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: health-checker
    release: green
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: health-checker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: health-checker
        release: green
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: golang:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 1Gi
        env:
        - name: REDIS_URL
          value: production",Deployment,8
369,Create a CronJob called model-trainer-cron in the data namespace. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It should have set to fire at 30 2 * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: model-trainer-cron
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: development
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: openjdk:17
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '1'
                memory: 128Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  suspend: false",CronJob,4
370,"Please configure a CronJob identified as load-balancer-cron within development. Make sure it has running on schedule 0 6 * * *, and also preserving the last 3 successful runs, and with the container labeled worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: 0 6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: busybox:16
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,6
371,"Provision a Service called dns-resolver-svc in the monitoring namespace. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It should have service type NodePort, accepting traffic on port 9090, while also forwarding to target port 9090, while also using TCP protocol, and tagged as team=platform.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
    team: platform
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: email-sender
  ports:
  - port: 9090
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,8
372,"Set up a Service called stream-consumer-svc in the monitoring namespace. It should have service type NodePort, while also communicating over UDP, and also accessible via port 3306.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3306""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    env: testing
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: session-store
  ports:
  - port: 3306
    targetPort: 8443
    protocol: UDP",Service,6
373,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name inventory-svc-ingress, deployed to data. Specifications include serving app.example.com, directing traffic to service worker-svc, additionally matching /ws.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/ws""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-svc""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-ingress
  namespace: data
spec:
  rules:
  - host: app.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: worker-svc
            port:
              number: 8080",Ingress,6
374,"Set up a Deployment called dns-resolver in the platform namespace. It should have maintaining 2 pods, and also carrying label tier: monitoring, additionally with the container labeled main, based on the rabbitmq:5.0 image, and serving on container port 3000.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
    tier: monitoring
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: dns-resolver
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: dns-resolver
        tier: monitoring
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: rabbitmq:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000",Deployment,8
375,Create a Pod called batch-processor-pod in the staging namespace. It should have built from bitnami/kafka:slim.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:slim""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
