389,"We need a Deployment named search-engine in logging. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires the container labeled search-engine, built from centos:latest, additionally running 1 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: search-engine
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: search-engine
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: search-engine
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: search-engine
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: search-engine
        image: centos:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        env:
        - name: WORKERS
          value: info",Deployment,6
390,"We need a Pod named image-processor-pod in staging. The configuration requires restart policy Never, tagged as tier=backend, running in a container named main, with the app label set to image-processor, and pulling ubuntu:8.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:8""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: image-processor-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: image-processor
    tier: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: ubuntu:8
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,8
391,"Set up a CronJob called scheduler-cron in the logging namespace. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. It should have triggered by cron expression */10 * * * *, and also restart mode set to Never, while also naming the container worker, and reserving 250m CPU resources.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/10 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""250m""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: scheduler-cron
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    team: infra
spec:
  schedule: '*/10 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: node:slim
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 250m
                memory: 256Mi
          restartPolicy: Never",CronJob,7
392,The rate-limiter Deployment operates in the development namespace. It includes exposing container port 5000. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. It has built from logstash:latest. It features naming the container server. It has maintaining 8 pods.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5000""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: rate-limiter
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: rate-limiter
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: rate-limiter
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: logstash:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 4Gi",Deployment,7
393,"We need a ConfigMap named webhook-relay-config in ml. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. The configuration requires where app_env contains pro, where app_name contains ima.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""ima""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""pro""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-config
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
data:
  workers: '8'
  rate_limit: '5000'
  app_env: production
  app_name: image-processor",ConfigMap,5
394,The cache-proxy-config ConfigMap operates in the data namespace. It requires having the feature_flags field. It has having feature_flags match the substring dar. It features where the app_name entry includes ord. It has mapping rate_limit to 1000.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""dar""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""ord""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-config
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: proxy-server
data:
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false
  app_env: development
  app_name: order-service
  rate_limit: '1000'",ConfigMap,7
395,"We need a Service named image-processor-svc in ml. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. The configuration requires selecting pods labeled app=health-checker, configured as ClusterIP, exposing port 1883, and with TCP as the transport protocol.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: image-processor-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: health-checker
  ports:
  - port: 1883
    targetPort: 1883
    protocol: TCP",Service,7
396,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name email-sender-cron, deployed to logging. Specifications include preserving the last 2 failed runs, executing on the */5 * * * * cron schedule, pulling nginx:16, with a restart policy of Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: email-sender-cron
  namespace: logging
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: nginx:16
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,7
397,"Set up a Deployment called feature-store in the data namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. It should have reserving 256Mi of memory, additionally maintaining 4 pods, with a CPU request of 1, while also built from centos:3.9, and the container identified as worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""256Mi""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: feature-store
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: centos:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: METRICS_PORT
          value: info",Deployment,8
398,"We need an Ingress named notification-svc-ingress in production. The configuration requires bound to host example.com, and also directing traffic to service notification-svc-svc, additionally capturing requests to /ws, serving on port 3000, and employing Exact path matching.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/ws""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-ingress
  namespace: production
spec:
  rules:
  - host: example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: notification-svc-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,8
399,"Please configure a Pod identified as search-engine-pod within default. Make sure it has running nginx:4.0, and with API_KEY configured as 8080.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: search-engine-pod
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: search-engine
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: nginx:4.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 6379
    env:
    - name: API_KEY
      value: '8080'",Pod,5
400,"Please configure an Ingress identified as worker-ingress within monitoring. Make sure it has the app label set to dns-resolver, handling traffic for app.example.com, matching /metrics, configured with pathType Exact.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/metrics""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: worker-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
spec:
  rules:
  - host: app.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /metrics
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: stream-consumer-svc
            port:
              number: 5000",Ingress,7
401,The frontend-pod Pod operates in the infra namespace. It features based on the httpd:14 image. It has the app label set to frontend. It is configured with OnFailure restart behavior.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:14""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: frontend-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: frontend
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: httpd:14
    ports:
    - containerPort: 6379
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,6
402,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name stream-consumer, deployed to monitoring. Specifications include with vault:1.2 as the base image, with a replica count of 8, the container identified as worker, and requesting 4Gi of memory.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4Gi""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    env: testing
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: stream-consumer
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: stream-consumer
        env: testing
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: vault:1.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 4Gi",Deployment,7
403,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name report-gen-pod, deployed to logging. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Specifications include configuring the DATABASE_URL variable, with env var DATABASE_URL assigned to debug, while also running httpd:21, tagged as tier=database.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""database""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""DATABASE_URL""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: report-gen-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: report-gen
    tier: database
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: httpd:21
    ports:
    - containerPort: 5000
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 1000m
        memory: 256Mi
    env:
    - name: DATABASE_URL
      value: debug",Pod,7
404,"We need a Pod named search-engine-pod in ml. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. The configuration requires running in a container named app, pulling prom/prometheus:3.9, needing 512Mi memory, and labeled app=search-engine.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""prom/prometheus:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""512Mi""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: search-engine-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: search-engine
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: prom/prometheus:3.9
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 512Mi
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,7
405,"Please configure a Deployment identified as notification-svc within staging. Make sure it has elasticsearch:1.2 as the base image, with 4 replicas, and also running in a container named notification-svc.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: notification-svc
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: notification-svc
    version: v1.0
    release: stable
    env: development
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: notification-svc
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: notification-svc
        version: v1.0
        release: stable
        env: development
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: notification-svc
        image: elasticsearch:1.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 64Mi
        env:
        - name: DEBUG
          value: 'true'",Deployment,6
406,The web-app-cron CronJob operates in the infra namespace. It features handling concurrent runs via Allow. It has the container labeled job. It has pulling vault:3.0. It has scheduled at */15 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/15 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""job""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Allow""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:3.0""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: web-app-cron
  namespace: infra
spec:
  schedule: '*/15 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: vault:3.0
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow",CronJob,7
407,"We need a Pod named batch-processor-pod in logging. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. The configuration requires labeled app=batch-processor, and also with env var SECRET_KEY assigned to info, annotated with env=production, additionally built from node:3.9.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""info""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: node:3.9
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    env:
    - name: SECRET_KEY
      value: info",Pod,7
408,The notification-svc-ingress Ingress operates in the monitoring namespace. It requires bound to host blog.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blog.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  rules:
  - host: blog.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: circuit-breaker-svc
            port:
              number: 80",Ingress,4
409,"We need an Ingress named circuit-breaker-ingress in logging. The configuration requires having the annotation ssl-redirect configured to /, and also bound to host beta.example.com, and enabling TLS on beta.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.ssl-redirect"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker-ingress
  namespace: logging
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: beta.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: ml-inference-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - beta.example.com
    secretName: circuit-breaker-tls",Ingress,6
410,"Provision a Pod called worker-pod in the ml namespace. It should have based on the mongo:3.1 image, with the app label set to worker, and the container identified as server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:3.1""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: worker-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: worker
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: mongo:3.1",Pod,6
411,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name user-service-ingress, deployed to data. Specifications include enabling TLS on beta.example.com, employing Exact path matching, using the user-service-tls TLS secret, routing requests to beta.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-tls""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: user-service-ingress
  namespace: data
  annotations:
    description: 'true'
  labels:
    env: development
spec:
  rules:
  - host: beta.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: batch-processor-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - beta.example.com
    secretName: user-service-tls",Ingress,7
412,The api-server-svc Service operates in the default namespace. It is configured with configured with ClientIP affinity. It is configured with exposed externally on port 31327. It is configured with UDP protocol. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. It includes listening on port 1883. It is configured with configured as NodePort.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.nodePort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""31327""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: api-server-svc
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: api-server
    tier: frontend
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: scheduler
  ports:
  - port: 1883
    targetPort: 8443
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 31327
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,8
413,"We need a Pod named health-checker-pod in production. The configuration requires listening on port 9200, based on the httpd:alpine image, with the JWT_SECRET environment variable.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""JWT_SECRET""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9200""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: health-checker-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: health-checker
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: httpd:alpine
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9200
    env:
    - name: JWT_SECRET
      value: 'false'",Pod,6
414,"Spin up an Ingress called proxy-server-ingress in the ml namespace. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. It should have secured via TLS secret proxy-server-tls, and also serving cdn.example.com, and bearing the label app=pdf-generator.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-ingress
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
spec:
  rules:
  - host: cdn.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: config-server-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - cdn.example.com
    secretName: proxy-server-tls",Ingress,6
415,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name web-app, deployed to logging. Specifications include naming the container app, running 8 copies, while also with a CPU request of 250m, pulling python:3.1.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""250m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-app
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: web-app
    tier: database
    env: production
    team: ml
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web-app
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web-app
        tier: database
        env: production
        team: ml
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: python:3.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 64Mi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: SECRET_KEY
          value: 'true'",Deployment,7
416,Set up a ConfigMap called order-service-config in the logging namespace. It should have log_level configured as debug.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: order-service-config
  namespace: logging
data:
  allowed_origins: https://example.com
  app_port: '5000'
  log_level: debug
  api_key_prefix: api-
  cache_ttl: '3600'",ConfigMap,4
417,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name feature-store, deployed to infra. Specifications include having 1 replicated pods, opening container port 5432, naming the container app, and also based on the rabbitmq:8 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    tier: database
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
        tier: database
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: rabbitmq:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: WORKERS
          value: '3'",Deployment,7
418,"Create a Pod called webhook-relay-pod in the development namespace. It should have whose container is called worker, with a restart policy of OnFailure, with env var APP_NAME assigned to production, running vault:1.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: webhook-relay
    team: ml
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: vault:1.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9092
    env:
    - name: APP_NAME
      value: production",Pod,7
419,"Configure a Service called config-server-svc in the data namespace. It should have selecting pods labeled app=order-service, listening on port 3000, via TCP, set up as NodePort, bearing the label team=ml.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: config-server-svc
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: config-server
    team: ml
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: order-service
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9092
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 31052",Service,8
420,"We need a Deployment named scheduler in data. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires naming the container scheduler, while also reserving 50m CPU resources, running openjdk:1.2, needing 512Mi memory, with a replica count of 4.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""512Mi""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: scheduler
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: scheduler
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: scheduler
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: scheduler
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: scheduler
        image: openjdk:1.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 4Gi
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: 'true'",Deployment,8
421,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name ml-inference-ingress, deployed to infra. Specifications include backed by service stream-consumer-svc, responding to requests for api.example.com, additionally with path matching set to Prefix.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-svc""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-ingress
  namespace: infra
spec:
  rules:
  - host: api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: stream-consumer-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - api.example.com
    secretName: ml-inference-tls",Ingress,6
422,"We need a Deployment named data-pipeline in monitoring. The configuration requires built from centos:3.9, with the container labeled main, with the team label set to ml, having 3 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    version: v1.0
    env: staging
    team: ml
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: data-pipeline
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: data-pipeline
        version: v1.0
        env: staging
        team: ml
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: centos:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: '8080'",Deployment,7
423,"Please configure a ConfigMap identified as payment-gateway-config within platform. Make sure it has a log_level entry present, and where the app_name entry includes wor.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""wor""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway-config
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    env: production
data:
  log_level: debug
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  max_connections: '200'
  app_name: worker",ConfigMap,5
424,The scheduler-pod Pod operates in the platform namespace. It has the container identified as runner. It is configured with rabbitmq:20 as the base image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: scheduler-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: scheduler
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: rabbitmq:20
    ports:
    - containerPort: 5000",Pod,5
425,Create a Pod called frontend-pod in the production namespace. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. It should have built from busybox:20.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:20""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: frontend-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: frontend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: busybox:20
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 200m
        memory: 4Gi",Pod,4
426,"Create a Deployment called payment-gateway in the monitoring namespace. It should have maintaining 8 pods, whose container is called main, based on the python:11 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: payment-gateway
    version: v3
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: payment-gateway
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: payment-gateway
        version: v3
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: python:11
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200",Deployment,6
427,"We need a Service named gateway-svc in staging. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires configured as ClusterIP, carrying label tier: frontend, and also via UDP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: gateway-svc
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: gateway
    tier: frontend
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: metrics-collector
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 443
    protocol: UDP",Service,6
428,The catalog-api-ingress Ingress operates in the ml namespace. It includes path matching set to ImplementationSpecific. It has handling traffic for status.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""status.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ImplementationSpecific""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: catalog-api-ingress
  namespace: ml
spec:
  rules:
  - host: status.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /admin
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: webhook-relay-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,5
429,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name health-checker-ingress, deployed to staging. Specifications include bound to host ws.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ws.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: health-checker-ingress
  namespace: staging
  annotations:
    proxy-body-size: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: ws.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: log-aggregator-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - ws.example.com
    secretName: health-checker-tls",Ingress,4
430,"Configure an Ingress called cache-proxy-ingress in the staging namespace. It should have responding to requests for v2.api.example.com, matching /graphql.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/graphql""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-ingress
  namespace: staging
