      value: 'true'",Pod,4
435,"Provision a Deployment called auth-service in the default namespace. It should have 2 replicas, pulling elasticsearch:3.0, and the container identified as server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: auth-service
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: auth-service
    tier: queue
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: auth-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: auth-service
        tier: queue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: elasticsearch:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,6
436,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name cron-runner-svc, deployed to platform. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. Specifications include set up as LoadBalancer, communicating over UDP, selecting pods labeled app=feature-store, and also with target port set to 8500.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8500""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-svc
  namespace: platform
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: feature-store
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 8500
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
437,"Please configure a Pod identified as api-server-pod within logging. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. Make sure it has pulling minio/minio:4.0, configuring the CACHE_TTL variable, running in a container named worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CACHE_TTL""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: api-server-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: api-server
    team: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: minio/minio:4.0
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
    env:
    - name: CACHE_TTL
      value: 'false'",Pod,6
438,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name session-store-pod, deployed to ml. Specifications include pulling images with policy Never, additionally built from elasticsearch:1.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: session-store-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: session-store
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: elasticsearch:1.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 443
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 256Mi
    env:
    - name: METRICS_PORT
      value: '8080'
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,5
439,"Set up a Deployment called cache-proxy in the logging namespace. It should have openjdk:3.0 as the base image, scaled to 1 instances, naming the container cache-proxy.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cache-proxy
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cache-proxy
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: cache-proxy
        image: openjdk:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        env:
        - name: JWT_SECRET
          value: 'false'",Deployment,6
440,"Please configure a Deployment identified as inventory-svc within platform. Make sure it has scaled to 2 instances, and also with the container labeled server, and also pulling envoyproxy/envoy:16, and employing Recreate for deployments.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: inventory-svc
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: inventory-svc
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: '8080'",Deployment,7
441,"Set up a ConfigMap called backend-config in the development namespace. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. It should have containing cache_ttl set to 300, while also containing app_port set to 3000, and also having the app_name field, mapping workers to 1, additionally where allowed_origins contains htt.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""300""}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""htt""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: backend-config
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
data:
  app_name: cache-proxy
  workers: '1'
  app_env: development
  allowed_origins: https://example.com
  app_port: '3000'
  cache_ttl: '300'",ConfigMap,8
442,The email-sender-pod Pod operates in the ml namespace. It includes bitnami/kafka:2.0 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:2.0""}]","apiVersion: v1
