          service:
            name: data-pipeline-svc
            port:
              number: 80",Ingress,7
444,"The event-bus-ingress Ingress operates in the production namespace. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. It features responding to requests for auth.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: event-bus-ingress
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: log-aggregator
spec:
  rules:
  - host: auth.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: order-service-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - auth.example.com
    secretName: event-bus-tls
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,4
445,"We need a Service named scheduler-svc in production. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. The configuration requires configured as NodePort, with sticky sessions via ClientIP, routing to backend port 27017, and operating on TCP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""27017""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: scheduler-svc
  namespace: production
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: auth-service
  ports:
  - port: 8500
    targetPort: 27017
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
446,The webhook-relay Deployment operates in the production namespace. It requires maintaining 8 pods. It features serving on container port 6379. It has whose container is called worker. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It requires based on the ruby:latest image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ruby:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: webhook-relay
    team: backend
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: webhook-relay
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: webhook-relay
        team: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: ruby:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: METRICS_PORT
          value: '60'",Deployment,7
447,The dns-resolver Deployment operates in the data namespace. It has having 8 replicated pods. It has the container identified as app. It has based on the httpd:latest image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
    version: v3.0
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: dns-resolver
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: dns-resolver
        version: v3.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: httpd:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 15672
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 2Gi
        env:
        - name: REDIS_URL
          value: 'true'",Deployment,6
448,The api-server Deployment operates in the ml namespace. It includes exposing container port 9200. It includes running 3 copies. It includes built from logstash:11. It is configured with whose container is called app.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9200""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: api-server
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: api-server
    release: blue
    env: testing
    version: v2
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: api-server
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: api-server
        release: blue
        env: testing
        version: v2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: logstash:11
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,7
449,"Please configure a Service identified as web-app-svc within infra. Make sure it has of type NodePort, annotated with env=production.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: web-app-svc
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: web-app
    env: production
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: session-store
  ports:
  - port: 443
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 31092
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
450,"We need a CronJob named notification-svc-cron in development. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The configuration requires the cron schedule 0 6 * * *, and also using Replace concurrency, while also with suspend set to false, and executing a command that begins with /bin/sh.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Replace""}, {""path"": ""spec.suspend"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""False""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: 0 6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: debian:17
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 750m
                memory: 128Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Replace
  suspend: false",CronJob,7
451,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name cron-runner, deployed to logging. Specifications include limited to 250m CPU, while also using alpine:14 as its container image, exposing container port 4222, having 1 replicated pods, and whose container is called server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""250m""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4222""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cron-runner
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
    tier: cache
    team: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cron-runner
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cron-runner
        tier: cache
        team: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: alpine:14
        ports:
        - containerPort: 4222
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 4Gi",Deployment,8
452,"Please configure an Ingress identified as health-checker-ingress within ml. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. Make sure it has annotated with rewrite-target set to true, directing traffic for the host api.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.rewrite-target"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""true""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: health-checker-ingress
  namespace: ml
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: 'true'
spec:
  rules:
  - host: api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /health
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,5
453,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name web-app-svc, deployed to data. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Specifications include operating as a ClusterIP service, and forwarding traffic to pods with app=image-processor.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: web-app-svc
  namespace: data
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: image-processor
  ports:
  - port: 8080
    targetPort: 9092
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
454,"We need a Pod named pdf-generator-pod in data. The configuration requires annotated with team=platform, additionally with the app label set to pdf-generator, with httpd:2.0 as the base image, pulling images with policy Always, and restart mode set to OnFailure.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:2.0""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pdf-generator-pod
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: httpd:2.0
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '2'
        memory: 1Gi
    env:
    - name: API_KEY
      value: '8080'
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,8
455,The worker-svc Service operates in the ml namespace. It features of type ClusterIP.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: worker-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: report-gen
  ports:
  - port: 6379
    targetPort: 6379
    protocol: TCP",Service,4
456,"Create an Ingress called backend-ingress in the logging namespace. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have routing requests to dashboard.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dashboard.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: backend-ingress
  namespace: logging
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: dashboard.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: session-store-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - dashboard.example.com
    secretName: backend-tls
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,4
457,"We need a ConfigMap named file-uploader-config in production. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. The configuration requires having max_connections=200 in its data, with feature_flags containing the text bet, containing the feature_flags entry, containing feature_flags set to beta=true, and having the cache_ttl field.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta=true""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""bet""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""200""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: file-uploader-config
  namespace: production
data:
  feature_flags: beta=true
  cache_ttl: '60'
  app_env: development
  database_url: mongodb://mongo:27017/app
  max_connections: '200'",ConfigMap,8
458,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name email-sender, deployed to infra. Specifications include pulling kibana:21, exposing container port 11211, whose container is called app, having 8 replicated pods, and bearing the label tier=database.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""11211""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""database""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: email-sender
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: email-sender
    tier: database
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: email-sender
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: email-sender
        tier: database
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: kibana:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,8
459,"Please configure a Deployment identified as report-gen within development. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. Make sure it has its container called server, built from logstash:11, additionally with 3 replicas, requesting 2 CPU.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: report-gen
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: report-gen
    tier: frontend
    version: v2
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: report-gen
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: report-gen
        tier: frontend
        version: v2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: logstash:11
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 64Mi
        env:
        - name: REDIS_URL
          value: info",Deployment,7
460,Please configure a Service identified as rate-limiter-svc within production. Make sure it has operating as a ClusterIP service.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}]","apiVersion: v1
