462,The cache-proxy Deployment operates in the ml namespace. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. It includes openjdk:4.0 as its container image. It has scaled to 5 instances. It has naming the container main.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
    release: green
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cache-proxy
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cache-proxy
        release: green
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: openjdk:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 256Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,6
463,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name data-pipeline-svc, deployed to infra. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Specifications include of type NodePort, operating on UDP, while also bearing the label team=ml, additionally selecting pods labeled app=catalog-api, additionally with a node port of 30853.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.nodePort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30853""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-svc
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    team: ml
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: catalog-api
  ports:
  - port: 1883
    targetPort: 80
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 30853",Service,8
464,"We need a Pod named auth-service-pod in staging. The configuration requires needing 128Mi memory, additionally running under service account monitoring-sa, running centos:21, while also allocated 50m CPU, additionally tagged with app: auth-service.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""128Mi""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring-sa""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}]","apiVersion: v1
