        memory: 128Mi
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,8
465,"Create a Service called batch-processor-svc in the platform namespace. It should have routing to pods where app is stream-consumer, while also serving on port 3000, as a LoadBalancer service.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-svc
  namespace: platform
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: stream-consumer
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: UDP",Service,6
466,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name user-service-svc, deployed to data. Specifications include operating on UDP, accepting traffic on port 443, and with service type LoadBalancer.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: user-service-svc
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: user-service
    env: testing
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: audit-logger
  ports:
  - port: 443
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: UDP",Service,6
467,"We need a Deployment named feature-store in data. The configuration requires built from consul:latest, additionally scaled to 10 instances, and whose container is called server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    version: v3.0
    tier: monitoring
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
        version: v3.0
        tier: monitoring
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: consul:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 256Mi",Deployment,6
468,The feature-store Deployment operates in the production namespace. It requires the container labeled server. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. It requires running busybox:3.0. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. It is configured with requesting 1000m CPU. It is configured with maintaining 8 pods.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: feature-store
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: busybox:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 4Gi
        env:
        - name: METRICS_PORT
          value: '8080'",Deployment,7
469,The health-checker-config ConfigMap operates in the platform namespace. It requires containing max_connections set to 200. It features mapping rate_limit to 100. It includes having database_url match the substring pos. It requires mapping database_url to postgres://db:5432/app. It has a cache_ttl entry present.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""pos""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres://db:5432/app""}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""200""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: health-checker-config
  namespace: platform
data:
  max_connections: '200'
  cache_ttl: '600'
  database_url: postgres://db:5432/app
  rate_limit: '100'
  retry_count: '10'
  app_env: staging",ConfigMap,8
470,"We need a Pod named gateway-pod in staging. The configuration requires based on the node:1.1 image, with the app label set to gateway, with port 15672 open, and also configured with IfNotPresent pull behavior, and using restart policy OnFailure.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:1.1""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""IfNotPresent""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: gateway-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: gateway
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: node:1.1
    ports:
    - containerPort: 15672
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '1'
        memory: 2Gi
    env:
    - name: NODE_ENV
      value: production
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Pod,8
471,The order-service-cron CronJob operates in the data namespace. It requires allocated 2 CPU. It has pulling envoyproxy/envoy:1.1. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It requires retaining 1 successful job records. It has executing on the 0 3 * * 1-5 cron schedule. It requires preserving the last 2 failed runs.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 3 * * 1-5""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: order-service-cron
  namespace: data
spec:
  schedule: 0 3 * * 1-5
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: envoyproxy/envoy:1.1
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '2'
                memory: 4Gi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,8
472,The gateway-pod Pod operates in the infra namespace. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It is configured with exposing port 3000. It includes pulling alpine:2.0.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: gateway-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: gateway
    tier: cache
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: alpine:2.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 3000
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 256Mi
    env:
    - name: APP_NAME
      value: debug
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,5
473,"We need an Ingress named batch-processor-ingress in data. The configuration requires bound to host dashboard.example.com, with a Exact pathType, and also directing traffic to service payment-gateway-svc.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dashboard.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-ingress
  namespace: data
spec:
  rules:
  - host: dashboard.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: payment-gateway-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,6
474,The webhook-relay-ingress Ingress operates in the staging namespace. It features handling the /api endpoint. It is configured with accepting traffic on port 8080. It requires responding to requests for status.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""status.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/api""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-ingress
  namespace: staging
spec:
  rules:
  - host: status.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: cache-proxy-svc
            port:
              number: 8080",Ingress,6
475,The notification-svc-config ConfigMap operates in the platform namespace. It requires where the workers field is 4.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
