476,"Deploy a Pod called rate-limiter-pod in the production namespace. It should have built from traefik:14, and also bearing the label team=ml, and with its container called app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""traefik:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: rate-limiter
    team: ml
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: traefik:14
    env:
    - name: LOG_LEVEL
      value: production",Pod,6
477,"Deploy a Pod called ssl-terminator-pod in the infra namespace. It should have pulling memcached:5.0, using service account admin, configuring the DATABASE_URL variable, and environment variable DATABASE_URL=false.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""memcached:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""DATABASE_URL""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: memcached:5.0
    env:
    - name: DATABASE_URL
      value: 'false'
  serviceAccountName: admin",Pod,7
478,"Set up a CronJob called metrics-collector-cron in the development namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. It should have its container called worker, reserving 50m CPU resources, running on schedule 0 0 * * 0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 0""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 0
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: ubuntu:11
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 50m
                memory: 2Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5",CronJob,6
479,The payment-gateway-pod Pod operates in the production namespace. It includes running openjdk:alpine. It is configured with pulling images with policy Always. It requires service account app-sa.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app-sa""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: payment-gateway
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: openjdk:alpine
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 250m
        memory: 2Gi
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: 'false'
    imagePullPolicy: Always
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,6
480,The report-gen Deployment operates in the platform namespace. It includes running ubuntu:1.0. It requires maintaining 5 pods. It is configured with naming the container worker.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: report-gen
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: report-gen
    team: backend
    release: canary
    version: v3.0
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: report-gen
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: report-gen
        team: backend
        release: canary
        version: v3.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: ubuntu:1.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: 'false'",Deployment,6
481,Set up an Ingress called user-service-ingress in the production namespace. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It should have routing requests to shop.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""shop.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: user-service-ingress
  namespace: production
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: shop.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /graphql
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: session-store-svc
            port:
              number: 8080",Ingress,4
482,"Spin up a ConfigMap called order-service-config in the platform namespace. It should have the app_env value including pro, and where app_port contains 300.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""pro""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""300""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: order-service-config
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    team: data
data:
  app_env: production
  log_level: warn
  app_name: order-service
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false
  api_key_prefix: pk-
  app_port: '3000'",ConfigMap,5
483,"Deploy a Deployment called webhook-relay in the development namespace. It should have needing 4Gi memory, while also maintaining 4 pods, with its container called webhook-relay, and also pulling debian:16, and with a RollingUpdate rollout strategy.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4Gi""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: webhook-relay
    version: v1.0
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: webhook-relay
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: webhook-relay
        version: v1.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: webhook-relay
        image: debian:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 1Gi",Deployment,8
484,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name cache-proxy-svc, deployed to infra. Specifications include with target port set to 11211, via TCP, with service type ClusterIP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""11211""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-svc
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
    team: infra
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: queue-worker
  ports:
  - port: 3306
    targetPort: 11211
    protocol: TCP",Service,6
485,"We need a Deployment named api-server in staging. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. The configuration requires mongo:11 as its container image, with 1 replicas, the container identified as app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: api-server
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: api-server
    version: v2.1
    tier: database
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: api-server
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: api-server
        version: v2.1
        tier: database
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: mongo:11
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 64Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,6
486,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name load-balancer-pod, deployed to platform. Specifications include labeled app=load-balancer, authenticated as service account default, running busybox:3.9, declaring the REDIS_URL env var.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""REDIS_URL""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: load-balancer
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: busybox:3.9
    ports:
    - containerPort: 1883
    env:
    - name: REDIS_URL
      value: 'true'
  serviceAccountName: default",Pod,7
487,"Please configure a Service identified as load-balancer-svc within production. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. Make sure it has as a LoadBalancer service, while also using UDP protocol, and forwarding traffic to pods with app=scheduler.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-svc
  namespace: production
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: scheduler
  ports:
  - port: 8200
    targetPort: 8200
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,6
488,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name inventory-svc-config, deployed to ml. Specifications include containing the rate_limit entry, including a max_connections data key.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-config
  namespace: ml
data:
  rate_limit: '500'
  max_connections: '50'",ConfigMap,5
489,Create a Pod called search-engine-pod in the platform namespace. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It should have ubuntu:11 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:11""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: search-engine-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: search-engine
    env: development
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: ubuntu:11
    ports:
    - containerPort: 11211
    env:
    - name: LOG_LEVEL
      value: info
  serviceAccountName: admin",Pod,4
490,The batch-processor-ingress Ingress operates in the default namespace. It is configured with the app label set to cdn-origin. It requires serving shop.example.com. It includes routed through the traefik ingress class. It requires handling the /graphql endpoint.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""shop.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/graphql""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""traefik""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-ingress
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    description: 'true'
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
spec:
  rules:
  - host: shop.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /graphql
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  ingressClassName: traefik",Ingress,7
491,"We need a Deployment named frontend in infra. The configuration requires scaled to 1 instances, naming the container main, running httpd:slim, additionally with CPU capped at 500m.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: frontend
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: frontend
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: httpd:slim
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 64Mi",Deployment,7
492,The batch-processor-cron CronJob operates in the staging namespace. It is configured with a restart policy of Never. It includes executing a command that begins with /bin/sh. It features the cron schedule */5 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: busybox:5.0
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - cleanup.sh
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,6
493,"We need an Ingress named event-bus-ingress in staging. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. The configuration requires directing traffic for the host auth.example.com, additionally forwarding requests to the dns-resolver-svc service, and employing Exact path matching.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: event-bus-ingress
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: auth.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /graphql
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: dns-resolver-svc
            port:
              number: 5000",Ingress,6
494,"Create an Ingress called audit-logger-ingress in the ml namespace. It should have ingressClassName set to haproxy, handling the /docs endpoint, serving staging.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""haproxy""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/docs""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: audit-logger-ingress
  namespace: ml
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
