506,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name cron-runner-svc, deployed to data. Specifications include using TCP protocol, exposing port 11211, with service type LoadBalancer, routing to backend port 8500, targeting pods with app=rate-limiter.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""11211""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8500""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-svc
  namespace: data
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: rate-limiter
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 8500
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
507,"Please configure a CronJob identified as proxy-server-cron within data. Make sure it has a CPU request of 1, retaining 3 successful job records, scheduled at 0 3 * * 1-5, and using restart policy Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 3 * * 1-5""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-cron
  namespace: data
spec:
  schedule: 0 3 * * 1-5
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: grafana/grafana:5.0
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '1'
                memory: 512Mi
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,7
508,We need a CronJob named rate-limiter-cron in logging. The configuration requires triggered by cron expression 0 12 * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 12 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-cron
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: config-server
spec:
  schedule: 0 12 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: grafana/grafana:3.0
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,4
509,"Configure a Pod called inventory-svc-pod in the production namespace. It should have listening on port 11211, while also pulling busybox:4.0, restarting on Always.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""11211""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: busybox:4.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 11211
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 128Mi
    imagePullPolicy: Always
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,6
510,Please configure a Pod identified as api-server-pod within staging. Make sure it has alpine:20 as the base image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:20""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: api-server-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: api-server
    tier: queue
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: alpine:20
    ports:
    - containerPort: 27017
    env:
    - name: PORT
      value: 'true'
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,4
511,"Configure a ConfigMap called auth-service-config in the logging namespace. It should have app_port containing the text 909, labeled env=testing, with max_connections configured as 200, and including a app_port data key.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""200""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""testing""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""909""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: auth-service-config
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    env: testing
data:
  debug_mode: 'false'
  app_port: '9090'
  max_connections: '200'",ConfigMap,7
512,The feature-store-cron CronJob operates in the staging namespace. It requires executing a command that begins with /bin/sh. It requires set to Replace concurrency mode. It is configured with the cron schedule 0 12 * * *. It requires keeping 3 successful job(s) in history.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 12 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Replace""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: feature-store-cron
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    team: ml
spec:
  schedule: 0 12 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: ruby:1.0
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Replace
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,7
513,"Please configure a Deployment identified as feature-store within staging. Make sure it has kibana:5.0 as the base image, and also with the container labeled main, with a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, maintaining 5 pods, and with JWT_SECRET defined in its environment.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""JWT_SECRET""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: feature-store
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: kibana:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 4222
        env:
        - name: JWT_SECRET
          value: production",Deployment,8
514,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name metrics-collector, deployed to data. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Specifications include with a replica count of 4, and also with consul:8 as the base image, and also with its container called metrics-collector, pulling images with policy Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    env: testing
    team: backend
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: metrics-collector
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: metrics-collector
        env: testing
        team: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: metrics-collector
        image: consul:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 128Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: 'false'",Deployment,7
515,"We need a Deployment named batch-processor in ml. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. The configuration requires pulling kibana:20, additionally running 5 copies, exposing container port 8080, with Recreate as the strategy type, whose container is called worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: batch-processor
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    version: v3
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: batch-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: batch-processor
        version: v3
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: kibana:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,8
516,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name service-mesh, deployed to platform. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Specifications include having 5 replicated pods, the container identified as worker, and also with a CPU request of 1000m, with node:alpine as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: service-mesh
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: service-mesh
    env: testing
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: service-mesh
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: service-mesh
        env: testing
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: node:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 1Gi",Deployment,7
517,"Configure a Deployment called data-pipeline in the default namespace. It should have golang:16 as its container image, running 10 copies, and also opening container port 8443, running in a container named main.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8443""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: data-pipeline
