585,"Spin up a Deployment called auth-service in the monitoring namespace. It should have configured with IfNotPresent pull behavior, based on the golang:4.0 image, the container identified as auth-service, and maintaining 6 pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""IfNotPresent""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: auth-service
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: auth-service
    env: staging
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: auth-service
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: auth-service
        env: staging
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: auth-service
        image: golang:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 512Mi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: PORT
          value: '60'",Deployment,7
586,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name gateway-config, deployed to default. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Specifications include where the rate_limit entry includes 100, while also where allowed_origins contains htt, labeled team=backend.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""htt""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""100""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: gateway-config
  namespace: default
  labels:
    team: backend
data:
  allowed_origins: https://example.com
  api_key_prefix: pk-
  app_name: backend
  rate_limit: '1000'",ConfigMap,6
587,The dns-resolver Deployment operates in the default namespace. It features pulling consul:3.9. It is configured with a replica count of 5. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It includes CPU capped at 1000m. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It includes its container called server.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: dns-resolver
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: dns-resolver
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: consul:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9090
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 64Mi",Deployment,7
588,The backend-pod Pod operates in the development namespace. It requires running logstash:17.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:17""}]","apiVersion: v1
