  rate_limit: '100'
  log_level: warn",ConfigMap,3
624,"Please configure a CronJob identified as worker-cron within default. Make sure it has the cron schedule */10 * * * *, retaining 3 successful job records, with a CPU request of 750m, while also based on the mongo:stable image, and with concurrency policy Allow.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/10 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Allow""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""750m""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: worker-cron
  namespace: default
spec:
  schedule: '*/10 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: mongo:stable
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - cleanup.sh
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 750m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,8
625,"We need a Deployment named worker in platform. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. The configuration requires running 2 copies, additionally running mongo:16, the container identified as worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: worker
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: worker
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: worker
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: worker
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: mongo:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,6
626,We need an Ingress named catalog-api-ingress in default. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. The configuration requires directing traffic for the host beta.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: catalog-api-ingress
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    description: 'true'
  labels:
    app: payment-gateway
spec:
  rules:
  - host: beta.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - beta.example.com
    secretName: catalog-api-tls",Ingress,4
627,"We need a ConfigMap named log-aggregator-config in platform. The configuration requires containing app_port set to 3000, where app_port contains 300, with the app label set to queue-worker, while also containing the allowed_origins entry.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""log-aggregator-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""300""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
