      containers:
      - name: cdn-origin
        image: bitnami/kafka:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: production",Deployment,8
644,The email-sender-cron CronJob operates in the monitoring namespace. It is configured with running on schedule 0 * * * *. It is configured with its container called cron. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. It has allocated 50m CPU.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: email-sender-cron
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  schedule: 0 * * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: python:8
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 50m
                memory: 2Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5",CronJob,6
645,"We need a CronJob named scheduler-cron in monitoring. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. The configuration requires set to Allow concurrency mode, set to fire at */30 * * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Allow""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: scheduler-cron
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: prom/prometheus:slim
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,5
646,"Please configure an Ingress identified as search-engine-ingress within infra. Make sure it has a Prefix pathType, with port 3000 open, routing requests to staging.example.com, and also with TLS enabled for host staging.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: search-engine-ingress
  namespace: infra
  annotations:
    description: /
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: analytics-engine-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - staging.example.com
    secretName: search-engine-tls",Ingress,7
647,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name search-engine-pod, deployed to platform. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. Specifications include authenticated as service account app-sa, built from openjdk:slim, while also restart mode set to OnFailure, reserving 64Mi of memory.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app-sa""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""64Mi""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: search-engine-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: search-engine
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: openjdk:slim
    ports:
    - containerPort: 4222
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 200m
        memory: 64Mi
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,7
648,"We need a Pod named pdf-generator-pod in platform. The configuration requires tagged with app: pdf-generator, based on the redis:8 image, and also declaring the WORKERS env var.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:8""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""WORKERS""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pdf-generator-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
    team: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: redis:8
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8080
    env:
    - name: WORKERS
      value: info",Pod,6
649,"Set up an Ingress called search-engine-ingress in the production namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. It should have routing requests to admin.example.com, with TLS termination using secret search-engine-tls, employing Exact path matching.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: search-engine-ingress
  namespace: production
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: backend-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - admin.example.com
    secretName: search-engine-tls",Ingress,6
650,"Please configure a Deployment identified as stream-consumer within logging. Make sure it has opening container port 4222, and also whose container is called worker, running consul:5.0, carrying label team: data, having 2 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4222""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    team: data
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: stream-consumer
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: stream-consumer
        team: data
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: consul:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 4222
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 512Mi",Deployment,8
651,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name metrics-collector-ingress, deployed to logging. Specifications include with path matching set to Prefix, additionally routing to backend service data-pipeline-svc, handling the /uploads endpoint, and directing traffic for the host dashboard.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dashboard.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/uploads""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-ingress
  namespace: logging
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: dashboard.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: data-pipeline-svc
            port:
              number: 80
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - dashboard.example.com
    secretName: metrics-collector-tls
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,7
652,"Provision a Deployment called backend in the infra namespace. It should have maintaining 6 pods, tagged as tier=monitoring, with openjdk:2.0 as the base image, with the container labeled server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: backend
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: backend
    tier: monitoring
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: backend
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: backend
        tier: monitoring
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: openjdk:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 15672
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: production",Deployment,7
653,"Please configure an Ingress identified as load-balancer-ingress within data. Make sure it has bearing the label env=development, routing requests to staging.example.com, serving on port 8080, with TLS using the secret load-balancer-tls, and with a Prefix pathType.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-ingress
  namespace: data
  labels:
    env: development
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /graphql
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: email-sender-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - staging.example.com
    secretName: load-balancer-tls
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,8
654,"Provision a Deployment called service-mesh in the ml namespace. It should have a replica count of 2, while also labeled team=devops, opening container port 9200, whose container is called server, and pulling ubuntu:21.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:21""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""devops""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9200""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: service-mesh
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: service-mesh
    team: devops
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: service-mesh
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: service-mesh
        team: devops
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: ubuntu:21
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 128Mi
        env:
        - name: WORKERS
          value: '60'",Deployment,8
655,"We need a Pod named ml-inference-pod in development. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. The configuration requires annotated with tier=cache, based on the kibana:alpine image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:alpine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: ml-inference
    tier: cache
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: kibana:alpine
    env:
    - name: SECRET_KEY
      value: '8080'",Pod,5
656,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name cdn-origin-cron, deployed to ml. Specifications include set to fire at */30 * * * *, and with nginx:3.1 as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx:3.1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin-cron
  namespace: ml
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: nginx:3.1
          restartPolicy: OnFailure",CronJob,5
657,"We need a ConfigMap named worker-config in development. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. The configuration requires having retry_count=5 in its data, containing log_level set to error.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""error""}, {""path"": ""data.retry_count"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: worker-config
  namespace: development
data:
  log_level: error
  retry_count: '5'
  database_url: mongodb://mongo:27017/app",ConfigMap,5
658,"Set up a ConfigMap called metrics-collector-config in the staging namespace. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. It should have log_level containing the text deb, with log_level configured as debug, where the rate_limit field is 100, while also storing cache_ttl with value 300.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""300""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""deb""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-config
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    team: platform
data:
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false
  cache_ttl: '300'
  log_level: debug
  rate_limit: '100'",ConfigMap,7
659,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name session-store, deployed to default. Specifications include using elasticsearch:stable as its container image, while also having 6 replicated pods, the container identified as main.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: session-store
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: session-store
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: session-store
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: session-store
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: elasticsearch:stable
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 4Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,6
660,The web-app-ingress Ingress operates in the monitoring namespace. It includes directing traffic for the host auth.example.com. It includes bearing the label app=gateway.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: web-app-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: gateway
spec:
  rules:
  - host: auth.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /health
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: pdf-generator-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,5
661,"Deploy a Deployment called config-server in the default namespace. It should have its container called server, while also scaled to 2 instances, and built from bitnami/kafka:slim.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: config-server
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: config-server
    version: v2.1
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: config-server
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: config-server
        version: v2.1
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: bitnami/kafka:slim
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 4Gi",Deployment,6
662,"Create a Service called cdn-origin-svc in the ml namespace. It should have labeled tier=monitoring, and also with target port set to 9092, and also using UDP protocol, selecting pods labeled app=order-service, with service type LoadBalancer.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9092""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin-svc
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
    tier: monitoring
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: order-service
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 9092
    protocol: UDP",Service,8
663,The ssl-terminator-pod Pod operates in the monitoring namespace. It features pulling postgres:1.0. This service was originally implemented in the monolith and is now being extracted as a microservice. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. It has declaring the SECRET_KEY env var. It features naming the container main. It requires listening on port 9090. It includes setting SECRET_KEY to true.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""SECRET_KEY""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""true""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: postgres:1.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9090
    env:
    - name: SECRET_KEY
      value: 'true'",Pod,8
664,"Set up a Service called frontend-svc in the infra namespace. It should have of type LoadBalancer, while also routing to pods where app is service-mesh.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh""}]","apiVersion: v1
