  name: pdf-generator-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
    env: testing
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: catalog-api
  ports:
  - port: 8080
    targetPort: 443
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
669,"Please configure a Service identified as order-service-svc within infra. Make sure it has forwarding to target port 9000, published on node port 30163, using UDP protocol, routing to pods where app is rate-limiter, and of type NodePort.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.nodePort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30163""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: order-service-svc
  namespace: infra
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: rate-limiter
  ports:
  - port: 8200
    targetPort: 9000
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 30163",Service,8
670,The frontend-ingress Ingress operates in the infra namespace. It requires managed by the istio ingress controller. It features routing requests to v2.api.example.com. It has enabling TLS on v2.api.example.com. It includes listening on port 80.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""istio""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""80""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: frontend-ingress
  namespace: infra
spec:
  rules:
  - host: v2.api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /ws
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 80
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - v2.api.example.com
    secretName: frontend-tls
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,7
671,"We need a Deployment named email-sender in production. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires the RollingUpdate deployment strategy, opening container port 5432, with 10 replicas, with the container labeled email-sender, with openjdk:4.0 as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: email-sender
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: email-sender
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: email-sender
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: email-sender
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: email-sender
        image: openjdk:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 1Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,8
672,The data-pipeline-config ConfigMap operates in the platform namespace. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It has containing the app_name entry. It has having app_name match the substring gat. It requires mapping redis_host to redis://cache:6379/0. It is configured with having the workers field. It has mapping log_level to debug.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""gat""}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis://cache:6379/0""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-config
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    env: development
data:
  app_name: gateway
  workers: '8'
  log_level: debug
  app_env: development
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  retry_count: '5'",ConfigMap,8
673,The inventory-svc Deployment operates in the production namespace. It requires a replica count of 1. It requires its container called worker. It features kibana:alpine as the base image. It is configured with TIMEOUT configured as false.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: inventory-svc
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: inventory-svc
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: kibana:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: 'false'",Deployment,7
674,"Create a Service called config-server-svc in the infra namespace. It should have accepting traffic on port 9090, and also operating on TCP, additionally configured with ClientIP affinity, and also as a NodePort service, and published on node port 31051.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.nodePort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""31051""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: config-server-svc
  namespace: infra
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: scheduler
  ports:
  - port: 9090
    targetPort: 27017
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 31051
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,8
675,"Please configure a Deployment identified as pdf-generator within logging. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. Make sure it has nginx:20 as the base image, and also with the container labeled main, and having 2 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: pdf-generator
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: pdf-generator
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: pdf-generator
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: nginx:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 64Mi",Deployment,6
676,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name inventory-svc-cron, deployed to logging. Specifications include with the cron schedule 0 6 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 6 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-cron
  namespace: logging
spec:
  schedule: 0 6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: kibana:2.0
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 500m
                memory: 128Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,4
677,"Provision an Ingress called feature-store-ingress in the platform namespace. It should have configured with pathType Prefix, bound to host staging.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: feature-store-ingress
  namespace: platform
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: 'true'
  labels:
    app: feature-store
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,5
678,"Please configure a Pod identified as data-pipeline-pod within logging. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Make sure it has a restart policy of Never, based on the ruby:1.0 image, and exposing the TIMEOUT environment variable.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ruby:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TIMEOUT""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    tier: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: ruby:1.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 4222
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: 'false'
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Pod,6
679,"Configure a ConfigMap called batch-processor-config in the production namespace. It should have mapping api_key_prefix to sk-, and also including a allowed_origins data key, and also mapping allowed_origins to *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.api_key_prefix"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""sk-""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-config
  namespace: production
data:
  allowed_origins: '*'
  api_key_prefix: sk-",ConfigMap,6
680,The rate-limiter-svc Service operates in the monitoring namespace. It has labeled env=production. It is configured with selecting pods labeled app=metrics-collector. It is configured with as a LoadBalancer service. It includes routing to backend port 8443.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8443""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: rate-limiter
    env: production
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: metrics-collector
  ports:
  - port: 5000
    targetPort: 8443
    protocol: TCP",Service,7
681,"Deploy a Deployment called cdn-origin in the platform namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It should have whose container is called worker, additionally with a replica count of 8, accepting connections on container port 1883, pulling centos:2.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
    env: testing
    tier: queue
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cdn-origin
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cdn-origin
        env: testing
        tier: queue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: centos:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,7
682,Configure a CronJob called worker-cron in the platform namespace. It should have set to fire at 30 2 * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: worker-cron
  namespace: platform
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: redis:11
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,4
683,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name ml-inference-config, deployed to infra. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Specifications include containing the debug_mode entry.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-config
  namespace: infra
data:
  debug_mode: 'true'
  retry_count: '10'
  feature_flags: enable_v2=true
  rate_limit: '500'
  database_url: mysql://db:3306/app",ConfigMap,4
684,Configure a Service called data-pipeline-svc in the development namespace. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It should have of type NodePort.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-svc
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    tier: queue
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: inventory-svc
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 30200",Service,4
685,"Deploy a Service called audit-logger-svc in the infra namespace. It should have TCP as the transport protocol, of type NodePort, while also matching pods carrying app=api-server, and labeled team=backend.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend""}]","apiVersion: v1
