689,The order-service-ingress Ingress operates in the ml namespace. It features directing traffic for the host admin.example.com. It has routing /admin requests. It includes annotated with app=cron-runner. It includes annotated with ssl-redirect set to 50m.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.ssl-redirect"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/admin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: order-service-ingress
  namespace: ml
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: 50m
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /admin
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: stream-consumer-svc
            port:
              number: 5000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - admin.example.com
    secretName: order-service-tls",Ingress,7
690,"We need a Service named web-app-svc in data. The configuration requires bearing the label env=testing, operating as a ClusterIP service, listening on port 3306, forwarding to target port 9200.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9200""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""testing""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3306""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: web-app-svc
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: web-app
    env: testing
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: pdf-generator
  ports:
  - port: 3306
    targetPort: 9200
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
691,The batch-processor-config ConfigMap operates in the default namespace. It has having rate_limit=1000 in its data.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-config
  namespace: default
data:
  workers: '2'
  debug_mode: 'false'
  log_level: error
  rate_limit: '1000'",ConfigMap,4
692,The metrics-collector Deployment operates in the infra namespace. It has the container labeled app. It has maintaining 5 pods. It features bearing the label env=testing. It is configured with exposing container port 443. It is configured with grafana/grafana:1.1 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana/grafana:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""testing""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    env: testing
    tier: database
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: metrics-collector
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: metrics-collector
        env: testing
        tier: database
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: grafana/grafana:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,8
693,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name session-store-svc, deployed to logging. Specifications include listening on port 1883, operating as a LoadBalancer service, labeled env=development, forwarding traffic to pods with app=auth-service.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: session-store-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: session-store
    env: development
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: auth-service
  ports:
  - port: 1883
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
694,"Configure an Ingress called email-sender-ingress in the development namespace. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. It should have backed by service model-trainer-svc, while also bearing the label app=session-store, having the annotation rewrite-target configured to true, while also with port 3000 open, and directing traffic for the host blog.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blog.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.rewrite-target"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""true""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: email-sender-ingress
  namespace: development
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: 'true'
  labels:
    app: session-store
spec:
  rules:
  - host: blog.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: model-trainer-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,8
695,"Please configure a Deployment identified as event-bus within development. Make sure it has scaled to 4 instances, and also with redis:5.0 as the base image, annotated with version=v1, the container identified as server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.version"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v1""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: event-bus
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: event-bus
    version: v1
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: event-bus
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: event-bus
        version: v1
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: redis:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883",Deployment,7
696,"Provision a Pod called file-uploader-pod in the staging namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It should have carrying the app=file-uploader label, allocated 50m CPU, and based on the redis:21 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:21""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: file-uploader-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: file-uploader
    env: staging
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: redis:21
    ports:
    - containerPort: 15672
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 1Gi
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: '8080'",Pod,6
697,"Set up a ConfigMap called service-mesh-config in the staging namespace. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have mapping log_level to debug, where the retry_count field is 10, having the max_connections field, where the max_connections field is 100.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.retry_count"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: service-mesh-config
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    env: staging
data:
  log_level: debug
  max_connections: '100'
  retry_count: '10'",ConfigMap,7
698,"We need a Deployment named health-checker in production. The configuration requires running kibana:2.0, additionally running in a container named main, with imagePullPolicy set to Never, with container port 27017, and also running 10 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""27017""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: health-checker
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: health-checker
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: health-checker
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: health-checker
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: kibana:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,8
699,"We need a Service named cron-runner-svc in ml. The configuration requires service type ClusterIP, additionally annotated with env=production.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-svc
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
    env: production
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: pdf-generator
  ports:
  - port: 15672
    targetPort: 5432
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
700,The feature-store Deployment operates in the platform namespace. It is configured with pulling ubuntu:alpine. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It includes naming the container feature-store. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It has a replica count of 3.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    env: development
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
        env: development
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: feature-store
        image: ubuntu:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: SECRET_KEY
          value: production",Deployment,6
701,"Configure a ConfigMap called circuit-breaker-config in the staging namespace. It should have database_url containing the text pos, storing app_port with value 3000, where the database_url field is postgres://db:5432/app, tagged as app=queue-worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres://db:5432/app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""pos""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker-config
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
data:
  debug_mode: 'true'
  database_url: postgres://db:5432/app
  workers: '1'
  app_port: '3000'",ConfigMap,7
702,"We need a Pod named search-engine-pod in logging. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. The configuration requires OnFailure restart behavior, configured with Never pull behavior, allocated 512Mi memory, additionally running openjdk:3.1, and with its container called worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""512Mi""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: search-engine-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: search-engine
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: openjdk:3.1
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 512Mi
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,8
703,"Provision a Service called cron-runner-svc in the staging namespace. It should have selecting pods labeled app=dns-resolver, forwarding to target port 3306, as a ClusterIP service, and using ClientIP session affinity.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3306""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-svc
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
    env: development
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: dns-resolver
  ports:
  - port: 443
    targetPort: 3306
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
704,The model-trainer-svc Service operates in the production namespace. It features as a LoadBalancer service. It has communicating over UDP.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: model-trainer-svc
  namespace: production
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: event-bus
  ports:
  - port: 8080
    targetPort: 11211
    protocol: UDP",Service,5
705,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name scheduler-cron, deployed to monitoring. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. Specifications include keeping 1 failed job(s) in history, pulling vault:latest, additionally retaining 5 successful job records, with OnFailure restart behavior, and set to fire at 0 12 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 12 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.successfulJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: scheduler-cron
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  schedule: 0 12 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: vault:latest
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,8
706,"Provision a ConfigMap called service-mesh-config in the logging namespace. It should have containing rate_limit set to 1000, additionally where the api_key_prefix field is pk-, having the cache_ttl field.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.api_key_prefix"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pk-""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: service-mesh-config
  namespace: logging
data:
  cache_ttl: '60'
  api_key_prefix: pk-
  workers: '2'
  rate_limit: '1000'",ConfigMap,6
707,"Please configure a Service identified as payment-gateway-svc within logging. Make sure it has targeting port 8080, communicating over TCP, and also of type LoadBalancer.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway-svc
  namespace: logging
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: report-gen
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: TCP",Service,6
708,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name order-service-config, deployed to production. Specifications include with the app_port value including 909, and also having app_port=9090 in its data, storing retry_count with value 3, with a timeout_seconds entry present, and including a app_port data key.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.timeout_seconds"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""data.retry_count"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""909""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: order-service-config
  namespace: production
data:
  timeout_seconds: '120'
  app_port: '9090'
  retry_count: '3'",ConfigMap,8
709,We need a CronJob named queue-worker-cron in default. The configuration requires set to fire at */30 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: queue-worker-cron
  namespace: default
  labels:
    env: production
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: grafana/grafana:16
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,4
710,"Please configure a Pod identified as ssl-terminator-pod within infra. Make sure it has labeled app=ssl-terminator, running node:14, declaring the METRICS_PORT env var, the container identified as app, restart mode set to Always.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""METRICS_PORT""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    tier: cache
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: node:14
    ports:
    - containerPort: 9200
    env:
    - name: METRICS_PORT
      value: debug",Pod,8
711,"Create an Ingress called notification-svc-ingress in the default namespace. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have including the description=50m annotation, and also backed by service stream-consumer-svc, bound to host auth.example.com, accepting traffic on port 80, and on path /api/v2.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.description"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""80""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/api/v2""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: notification-svc-ingress
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    description: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: auth.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v2
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: stream-consumer-svc
            port:
              number: 80",Ingress,8
712,"Create a Deployment called queue-worker in the logging namespace. It should have consul:latest as its container image, additionally running in a container named server, running 2 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: queue-worker
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
    team: frontend
    tier: backend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: queue-worker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: queue-worker
        team: frontend
        tier: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: consul:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 1Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,6
713,The email-sender-svc Service operates in the staging namespace. It includes configured as NodePort. It features proxying to port 5432 on the backend.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: email-sender-svc
  namespace: staging
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: feature-store
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 5432
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 31195
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
714,"Please configure a Deployment identified as auth-service within logging. Make sure it has python:20 as the base image, having 10 replicated pods, reserving 512Mi of memory, additionally with its container called worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""512Mi""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: auth-service
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: auth-service
    tier: cache
    env: production
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: auth-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: auth-service
        tier: cache
        env: production
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: python:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: PORT
          value: 'false'",Deployment,7
715,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name image-processor-cron, deployed to logging. Specifications include launching with the /bin/sh command prefix, set to fire at 0 0 * * 0, and requesting 250m CPU.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 0""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""250m""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: image-processor-cron
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    team: platform
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 0
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: alpine:1.1
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 250m
                memory: 2Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 5",CronJob,6
716,"Spin up a Deployment called metrics-collector in the development namespace. It should have scaled to 3 instances, with its container called server, and pulling envoyproxy/envoy:17.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:17""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    env: production
    tier: queue
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: metrics-collector
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: metrics-collector
        env: production
        tier: queue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:17
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 4Gi
        env:
        - name: JWT_SECRET
          value: '8080'",Deployment,6
717,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name payment-gateway-svc, deployed to development. Specifications include configured as ClusterIP, and also using ClientIP session affinity, and also accepting traffic on port 9092, and operating on TCP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9092""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway-svc
  namespace: development
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: inventory-svc
  ports:
  - port: 9092
    targetPort: 8500
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
718,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name image-processor-config, deployed to logging. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: image-processor-config
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
data:
  api_key_prefix: api-
  debug_mode: 'false'
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  app_name: web-app",ConfigMap,3
719,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name circuit-breaker, deployed to monitoring. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Specifications include running elasticsearch:16, reserving 2 CPU resources, and also naming the container app, and also allocated 128Mi memory, additionally having 2 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""128Mi""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: circuit-breaker
    tier: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: circuit-breaker
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: circuit-breaker
        tier: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: elasticsearch:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 2Gi",Deployment,8
720,"Configure an Ingress called rate-limiter-ingress in the platform namespace. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. It should have responding to requests for status.example.com, and employing Prefix path matching.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""status.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-ingress
  namespace: platform
spec:
  rules:
  - host: status.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /admin
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: frontend-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,5
721,"Provision a CronJob called gateway-cron in the ml namespace. It should have set to fire at 0 0 * * 0, and using restart policy Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 0""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: gateway-cron
  namespace: ml
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 0
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: ubuntu:3.0
          restartPolicy: Never
  suspend: false
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 3
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,5
722,"Provision a Deployment called feature-store in the staging namespace. It should have scaled to 2 instances, and also with the container labeled server, with consul:stable as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    tier: backend
    team: platform
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
        tier: backend
        team: platform
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: consul:stable
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8500
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 1Gi
        env:
        - name: PORT
          value: info",Deployment,6
723,"We need a Deployment named batch-processor in default. The configuration requires deployed via Recreate, and also bearing the label env=testing, built from nats:1.1, maintaining 4 pods, and naming the container app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""testing""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: batch-processor
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    env: testing
    release: green
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: batch-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: batch-processor
        env: testing
        release: green
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: nats:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        env:
        - name: TIMEOUT
          value: info",Deployment,8
724,The scheduler-config ConfigMap operates in the production namespace. It has storing rate_limit with value 500.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: scheduler-config
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: ml-inference
data:
  api_key_prefix: sk-
  database_url: mongodb://mongo:27017/app
  rate_limit: '500'",ConfigMap,4
725,"Configure a CronJob called web-app-cron in the staging namespace. It should have busybox:stable as the base image, scheduled at */5 * * * *, actively running (not suspended), with a restart policy of Never, with its command starting with python.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.suspend"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""False""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:stable""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: web-app-cron
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    team: devops
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: busybox:stable
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  suspend: false",CronJob,8
726,"Please configure an Ingress identified as scheduler-ingress within default. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Make sure it has matching /uploads, additionally responding to requests for shop.example.com, with ingressClassName set to istio.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""shop.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""istio""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/uploads""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: scheduler-ingress
  namespace: default
spec:
  rules:
  - host: shop.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: dns-resolver-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - shop.example.com
    secretName: scheduler-tls
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,6
727,Create a Pod called cron-runner-pod in the staging namespace. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. It should have built from redis:3.0.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:3.0""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: cron-runner-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: redis:3.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 15672",Pod,4
728,"Please configure a ConfigMap identified as catalog-api-config within platform. Make sure it has where allowed_origins contains htt, carrying label team: data, containing the app_port entry.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""htt""}]","apiVersion: v1
