            memory: 2Gi
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: '60'",Deployment,6
741,The rate-limiter-pod Pod operates in the logging namespace. It has Always restart behavior. It requires nginx:1.2 as the base image. It includes needing 1 of CPU. It is configured with service account monitoring-sa.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring-sa""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: rate-limiter
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: nginx:1.2
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '1'
        memory: 256Mi
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,7
742,"Please configure a CronJob identified as auth-service-cron within staging. Make sure it has running on schedule */15 * * * *, additionally allocated 750m CPU, and actively running (not suspended).","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""auth-service-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/15 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.suspend"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""False""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""750m""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: auth-service-cron
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    team: infra
spec:
  schedule: '*/15 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: consul:5.0
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 750m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  suspend: false
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 3",CronJob,6
743,"Provision a Service called webhook-relay-svc in the logging namespace. It should have via UDP, annotated with tier=database, targeting port 80, with service type NodePort, and selecting pods labeled app=analytics-engine.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""80""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""analytics-engine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""database""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: webhook-relay
    tier: database
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: analytics-engine
  ports:
  - port: 5432
    targetPort: 80
    protocol: UDP",Service,8
744,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name log-aggregator-ingress, deployed to ml. Specifications include directing traffic to service load-balancer-svc, additionally with the env label set to production, accepting traffic on port 443, while also handling traffic for v2.api.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""log-aggregator-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: log-aggregator-ingress
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    env: production
spec:
  rules:
  - host: v2.api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: load-balancer-svc
            port:
              number: 443",Ingress,7
745,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name search-engine-svc, deployed to logging. Specifications include proxying to port 9090 on the backend, configured as LoadBalancer.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: search-engine-svc
  namespace: logging
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: cron-runner
  ports:
  - port: 8500
    targetPort: 9090
    protocol: UDP",Service,5
746,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name email-sender-ingress, deployed to platform. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. Specifications include tagged as env=staging, backed by service cdn-origin-svc, responding to requests for v2.api.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: email-sender-ingress
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    env: staging
spec:
  rules:
  - host: v2.api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: cdn-origin-svc
            port:
              number: 443",Ingress,6
747,The frontend-pod Pod operates in the development namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It features built from minio/minio:16. It features OnFailure restart behavior.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: frontend-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: frontend
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: minio/minio:16
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 750m
        memory: 128Mi
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,5
748,The user-service Deployment operates in the platform namespace. It has scaled to 8 instances. It features container port 9000. It includes traefik:20 as the base image. It has its container called worker.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""traefik:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: user-service
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: user-service
    release: green
    version: v2.0
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: user-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: user-service
        release: green
        version: v2.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: traefik:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: '60'",Deployment,7
749,"Provision a Deployment called gateway in the ml namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. It should have the container identified as server, scaled to 3 instances, and based on the mongo:1.1 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: gateway
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: gateway
    release: blue
    env: testing
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: gateway
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: gateway
        release: blue
        env: testing
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: mongo:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 1Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: JWT_SECRET
          value: '8080'",Deployment,6
750,"Please configure a ConfigMap identified as proxy-server-config within production. Make sure it has containing the app_env entry, with a app_name entry present.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-config
  namespace: production
data:
  app_env: production
  app_name: payment-gateway",ConfigMap,5
751,"We need a Deployment named notification-svc in monitoring. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. The configuration requires scaled to 10 instances, while also with its container called main, running openjdk:2.0, and with RollingUpdate as the strategy type.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: notification-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: notification-svc
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: notification-svc
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: notification-svc
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: openjdk:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 256Mi",Deployment,7
752,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name worker-svc, deployed to staging. Specifications include with the tier label set to queue, routing to backend port 3000, communicating over UDP, and also of type NodePort.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3000""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.tier"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: worker-svc
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: worker
    tier: queue
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: proxy-server
  ports:
  - port: 8443
    targetPort: 3000
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
753,The load-balancer-pod Pod operates in the staging namespace. It features having LOG_LEVEL set to debug. It includes busybox:1.2 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: load-balancer
    tier: monitoring
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: busybox:1.2
    ports:
    - containerPort: 1883
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 200m
        memory: 1Gi
    env:
    - name: LOG_LEVEL
      value: debug",Pod,5
754,"Please configure a ConfigMap identified as rate-limiter-config within development. Make sure it has app_env configured as staging, with app_env containing the text sta, and where the app_port field is 9090.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rate-limiter-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""data.app_port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""sta""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter-config
  namespace: development
data:
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false
  timeout_seconds: '120'
  app_port: '9090'
  app_env: staging
  retry_count: '5'
  max_connections: '200'",ConfigMap,6
755,We need a Service named session-store-svc in staging. The configuration requires of type NodePort.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: session-store-svc
  namespace: staging
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: session-store
  ports:
  - port: 9092
    targetPort: 8500
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,4
756,Please configure an Ingress identified as cache-proxy-ingress within staging. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Make sure it has handling traffic for shop.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""shop.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-ingress
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: shop.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v1
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: inventory-svc-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,4
757,"Please configure a Service identified as search-engine-svc within logging. Make sure it has of type LoadBalancer, serving on port 15672.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: search-engine-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: search-engine
    team: backend
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: cdn-origin
  ports:
  - port: 15672
    targetPort: 8500
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,5
758,Spin up a ConfigMap called session-store-config in the data namespace. It should have mapping app_name to gateway.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: session-store-config
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: worker
data:
  timeout_seconds: '120'
  app_name: gateway
  api_key_prefix: api-
  rate_limit: '5000'",ConfigMap,4
759,"Spin up a Service called feature-store-svc in the platform namespace. It should have proxying to port 6379 on the backend, while also configured as NodePort, and targeting pods with app=report-gen.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: feature-store-svc
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    team: platform
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: report-gen
  ports:
  - port: 443
    targetPort: 6379
    protocol: TCP
    nodePort: 30842",Service,6
760,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name ssl-terminator-svc, deployed to production. Specifications include of type ClusterIP, matching pods carrying app=email-sender, forwarding to target port 8080, and operating on UDP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: development
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: email-sender
  ports:
  - port: 8080
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
761,The ssl-terminator Deployment operates in the production namespace. It has 10 replicas. It requires labeled version=v2.0. It requires kibana:16 as the base image. It is configured with running in a container named ssl-terminator.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.version"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.0""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: ssl-terminator
    env: testing
    version: v2.0
    team: devops
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: ssl-terminator
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: ssl-terminator
        env: testing
        version: v2.0
        team: devops
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: ssl-terminator
        image: kibana:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        env:
        - name: NODE_ENV
          value: '3'",Deployment,7
762,"Please configure a Pod identified as catalog-api-pod within monitoring. Make sure it has running kibana:alpine, with a restart policy of Never, and bearing the app label catalog-api.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:alpine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: catalog-api-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: catalog-api
    env: development
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: kibana:alpine
    ports:
    - containerPort: 3306
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,6
763,"Please configure an Ingress identified as gateway-ingress within platform. Make sure it has bound to host admin.example.com, and using the gateway-tls TLS secret.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: gateway-ingress
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: circuit-breaker-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - admin.example.com
    secretName: gateway-tls
  ingressClassName: haproxy",Ingress,5
764,"Please configure a Deployment identified as cdn-origin within platform. Make sure it has a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, with its container called cdn-origin, scaled to 4 instances, with vault:16 as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cdn-origin
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cdn-origin
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: cdn-origin
        image: vault:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000",Deployment,7
765,"Please configure a Service identified as metrics-collector-svc within monitoring. Make sure it has routing to pods where app is analytics-engine, and also set up as LoadBalancer, accessible via port 5432, bearing the label team=ml.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""analytics-engine""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-svc
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    team: ml
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: analytics-engine
  ports:
  - port: 5432
    targetPort: 6379
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
766,"Spin up a Service called event-bus-svc in the ml namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. It should have proxying to port 443 on the backend, as a ClusterIP service, with UDP as the transport protocol, exposing port 9090.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9090""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: event-bus-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: ml-inference
  ports:
  - port: 9090
    targetPort: 443
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
767,Spin up a Pod called inventory-svc-pod in the staging namespace. It should have built from debian:1.1.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:1.1""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
    tier: frontend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: debian:1.1
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 50m
        memory: 64Mi
    env:
    - name: DEBUG
      value: debug",Pod,4
768,The image-processor Deployment operates in the monitoring namespace. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. It requires running grafana/grafana:1.1. It includes the container identified as image-processor. It is configured with requesting 50m CPU. It requires a replica count of 2.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana/grafana:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: image-processor
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: image-processor
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: image-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: image-processor
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: image-processor
        image: grafana/grafana:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi",Deployment,7
769,"We need a Deployment named feature-store in platform. The configuration requires tagged as env=staging, naming the container feature-store, with a replica count of 10, and running python:8.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""feature-store""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: feature-store
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: feature-store
    env: staging
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: feature-store
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: feature-store
        env: staging
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: feature-store
        image: python:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 2Gi",Deployment,7
770,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name metrics-collector-config, deployed to data. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-config
  namespace: data
data:
  app_name: log-aggregator
  log_level: warn
  cache_ttl: '600'
  rate_limit: '500'",ConfigMap,3
771,"Create a Deployment called event-bus in the default namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It should have running redis:3.1, scaled to 5 instances, and also with its container called server, and serving on container port 8200.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8200""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: event-bus
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: event-bus
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: event-bus
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: event-bus
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: redis:3.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8200
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: CACHE_TTL
          value: '8080'",Deployment,7
772,The webhook-relay-pod Pod operates in the logging namespace. It requires setting CACHE_TTL to true. It is configured with built from mysql:alpine.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mysql:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""true""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: webhook-relay
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: mysql:alpine
    ports:
    - containerPort: 5000
    env:
    - name: CACHE_TTL
      value: 'true'
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: monitoring-sa",Pod,5
773,"Spin up a Deployment called gateway in the monitoring namespace. It should have pulling logstash:1.2, while also with the container labeled gateway, maintaining 2 pods, and using the Recreate deployment strategy.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: gateway
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: gateway
    version: v1
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: gateway
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: gateway
        version: v1
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: gateway
        image: logstash:1.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 1Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: info",Deployment,7
774,"Please configure a Deployment identified as gateway within infra. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Make sure it has running in a container named main, labeled release=green, pulling kibana:alpine, and also having 4 replicated pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.release"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""green""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: gateway
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: gateway
    env: testing
    release: green
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: gateway
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: gateway
        env: testing
        release: green
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: kibana:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,7
775,"Please configure a ConfigMap identified as stream-consumer-config within default. Make sure it has a workers entry present, including a redis_host data key, and also where the redis_host entry includes red, and where the workers field is 1.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.workers"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""red""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer-config
  namespace: default
data:
  workers: '1'
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  cache_ttl: '60'",ConfigMap,7
776,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name scheduler-pod, deployed to infra. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. Specifications include labeled app=scheduler, using mysql:11 as its container image, whose container is called runner, and restart mode set to Always.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mysql:11""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: scheduler-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: scheduler
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: mysql:11",Pod,7
777,"Create a Pod called circuit-breaker-pod in the infra namespace. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. It should have SECRET_KEY configured as production, additionally configuring the SECRET_KEY variable, and using redis:slim as its container image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""redis:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""SECRET_KEY""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: circuit-breaker
    env: testing
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: redis:slim
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8500
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 200m
        memory: 128Mi
    env:
    - name: SECRET_KEY
      value: production",Pod,6
778,"Deploy a Deployment called audit-logger in the production namespace. It should have maintaining 1 pods, whose container is called audit-logger, needing 1 of CPU, and based on the minio/minio:8 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: audit-logger
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: audit-logger
    version: v1
    team: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: audit-logger
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: audit-logger
        version: v1
        team: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: audit-logger
        image: minio/minio:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 4Gi",Deployment,7
779,The batch-processor Deployment operates in the platform namespace. It requires its container called main. It is configured with centos:16 as the base image. It requires maintaining 10 pods.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: batch-processor
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    version: v3
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: batch-processor
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: batch-processor
        version: v3
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: centos:16
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092",Deployment,6
780,"We need a Service named ml-inference-svc in development. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The configuration requires targeting port 15672, via UDP, and also with service type ClusterIP, and tagged as env=development.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml-inference-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: ml-inference-svc
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: ml-inference
    env: development
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: worker
  ports:
  - port: 1883
    targetPort: 15672
    protocol: UDP",Service,7
781,We need a ConfigMap named backend-config in monitoring. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. The configuration requires having debug_mode match the substring fal.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""fal""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: backend-config
  namespace: monitoring
data:
  redis_host: redis://cache:6379/0
  max_connections: '100'
  feature_flags: dark_mode=false
  debug_mode: 'false'
  log_level: info
  rate_limit: '1000'",ConfigMap,4
782,"Spin up a CronJob called audit-logger-cron in the development namespace. It should have its command starting with /bin/sh, with the env label set to staging, with concurrency policy Forbid, with the cron schedule 0 3 * * 1-5.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 3 * * 1-5""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Forbid""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: audit-logger-cron
  namespace: development
  labels:
    env: staging
spec:
  schedule: 0 3 * * 1-5
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: postgres:20
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo done
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid",CronJob,7
783,The worker-svc Service operates in the infra namespace. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It requires sticky sessions via ClientIP. It is configured with forwarding traffic to pods with app=queue-worker. It features TCP as the transport protocol. It features forwarding to target port 9000. It requires set up as ClusterIP.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9000""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: worker-svc
  namespace: infra
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: queue-worker
  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 9000
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,8
784,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name image-processor, deployed to default. Specifications include naming the container app, pulling rabbitmq:1.1, with 8 replicas, opening container port 5432, and exposing the LOG_LEVEL environment variable.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LOG_LEVEL""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: image-processor
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: image-processor
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: image-processor
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: image-processor
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: rabbitmq:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 512Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: LOG_LEVEL
          value: '3'",Deployment,8
785,"We need a Deployment named metrics-collector in logging. The configuration requires having 8 replicated pods, built from minio/minio:4.0, the container identified as main.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: metrics-collector
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: metrics-collector
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: minio/minio:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 4Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 64Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,6
786,"Deploy a Deployment called circuit-breaker in the ml namespace. It should have configuring the LOG_LEVEL variable, maintaining 4 pods, and also running openjdk:3.9, with env var LOG_LEVEL assigned to false, and running in a container named server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LOG_LEVEL""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: circuit-breaker
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: circuit-breaker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: circuit-breaker
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: openjdk:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        env:
        - name: LOG_LEVEL
          value: 'false'",Deployment,8
787,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name service-mesh-svc, deployed to data. Specifications include exposing port 5000, while also selecting pods labeled app=audit-logger, with service type LoadBalancer, forwarding to target port 4222, and with TCP as the transport protocol.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5000""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4222""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: service-mesh-svc
  namespace: data
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: audit-logger
  ports:
  - port: 5000
    targetPort: 4222
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
788,The backend-config ConfigMap operates in the infra namespace. It features having retry_count=5 in its data. It has which includes a cache_ttl key. It is configured with including a rate_limit data key. It is configured with having cache_ttl=300 in its data. It features rate_limit configured as 5000.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""300""}, {""path"": ""data.retry_count"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: backend-config
  namespace: infra
data:
  cache_ttl: '300'
  rate_limit: '5000'
  retry_count: '5'
  max_connections: '10'
  timeout_seconds: '30'",ConfigMap,8
789,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name webhook-relay-cron, deployed to platform. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Specifications include scheduled at */5 * * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-cron
  namespace: platform
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: job
            image: prom/prometheus:3.0
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 250m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure",CronJob,4
790,"We need a Pod named proxy-server-pod in data. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. The configuration requires the container identified as runner, based on the rabbitmq:slim image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-pod
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: proxy-server
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: rabbitmq:slim
    ports:
    - containerPort: 1883
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '1'
        memory: 2Gi
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,5
791,"We need a CronJob named file-uploader-cron in staging. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The configuration requires restart policy Never, set to fire at 0 0 * * *, and pulling mongo:17.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mongo:17""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: file-uploader-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: cron
            image: mongo:17
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 1000m
                memory: 512Mi
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,6
792,"We need a Service named ssl-terminator-svc in platform. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. The configuration requires communicating over UDP, of type ClusterIP, matching pods carrying app=cdn-origin, and using ClientIP session affinity.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-svc
  namespace: platform
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: cdn-origin
  ports:
  - port: 8200
    targetPort: 9092
    protocol: UDP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,7
793,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name health-checker-pod, deployed to development. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. Specifications include labeled env=production, and also with the app label set to health-checker, pulling vault:8, and using restart policy Always.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""vault:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: health-checker-pod
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: health-checker
    env: production
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: vault:8",Pod,7
794,The image-processor-pod Pod operates in the monitoring namespace. It is configured with Always restart behavior. It has based on the elasticsearch:8 image. It features running in a container named runner. It has env var CACHE_TTL assigned to debug.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""elasticsearch:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debug""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: image-processor-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: image-processor
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
