            memory: 128Mi",Deployment,6
812,"Configure a ConfigMap called report-gen-config in the staging namespace. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It should have redis_host containing the text red, and also with the app_env value including sta, and containing max_connections set to 100.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.app_env"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""sta""}, {""path"": ""data.max_connections"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100""}, {""path"": ""data.redis_host"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""red""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: report-gen-config
  namespace: staging
data:
  redis_host: redis://redis-master:6379
  feature_flags: enable_v2=true
  max_connections: '100'
  app_env: staging",ConfigMap,6
813,"Spin up an Ingress called worker-ingress in the staging namespace. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. It should have serving on port 5000, routing requests to grafana.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5000""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: worker-ingress
  namespace: staging
  annotations:
    description: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: grafana.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /admin
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: pdf-generator-svc
            port:
              number: 5000",Ingress,5
814,"Set up a Pod called inventory-svc-pod in the infra namespace. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The data processed by this service is classified as PII and must comply with GDPR requirements. It should have a memory request of 128Mi, and based on the logstash:20 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logstash:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""128Mi""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: logstash:20
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8200
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '1'
        memory: 128Mi",Pod,5
815,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name scheduler-config, deployed to staging. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Specifications include storing app_name with value email-sender, having database_url match the substring pos, mapping cache_ttl to 600, additionally which includes a feature_flags key, and having database_url=postgres://db:5432/app in its data.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""scheduler-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres://db:5432/app""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""600""}, {""path"": ""data.database_url"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""pos""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: scheduler-config
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: load-balancer
data:
  cache_ttl: '600'
  feature_flags: beta=true
  app_name: email-sender
  database_url: postgres://db:5432/app",ConfigMap,8
816,The webhook-relay-cron CronJob operates in the logging namespace. It has a restart policy of Never. It includes pulling mysql:16. It includes requesting 100m CPU. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. It features running on schedule 30 2 * * *. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. It has the team label set to ml.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""30 2 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""mysql:16""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100m""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-cron
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    team: ml
spec:
  schedule: 30 2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: mysql:16
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 100m
                memory: 256Mi
          restartPolicy: Never",CronJob,8
817,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name pdf-generator, deployed to data. Specifications include naming the container worker, while also having 10 replicated pods, and running nats:4.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""pdf-generator""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: pdf-generator
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: pdf-generator
    version: v1
    team: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: pdf-generator
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: pdf-generator
        version: v1
        team: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: nats:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 4Gi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,6
818,"Please configure a Service identified as config-server-svc within production. Make sure it has communicating over TCP, additionally routing to backend port 15672, selecting pods labeled app=webhook-relay, configured as ClusterIP, bearing the label team=platform.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: config-server-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: config-server
    team: platform
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: webhook-relay
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 15672
    protocol: TCP",Service,8
819,"We need a CronJob named file-uploader-cron in monitoring. The configuration requires allocated 2 CPU, executing on the 0 0 1 * * cron schedule, with its command starting with /bin/sh, built from nats:alpine, with a restart policy of Never.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 1 * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: file-uploader-cron
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 1 * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: nats:alpine
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - cleanup.sh
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: '2'
                memory: 128Mi
          restartPolicy: Never",CronJob,8
820,"We need a Deployment named file-uploader in monitoring. The configuration requires a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, based on the prom/prometheus:latest image, running 10 copies, and also reserving 1 CPU resources, and with the container labeled app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""prom/prometheus:latest""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: file-uploader
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: file-uploader
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: file-uploader
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: file-uploader
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: prom/prometheus:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 1Gi
        env:
        - name: API_KEY
          value: 'true'",Deployment,8
821,"Create a Deployment called cdn-origin in the infra namespace. It should have debian:11 as its container image, running in a container named app, additionally annotated with release=green, and running 10 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.release"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""green""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
