829,We need an Ingress named gateway-ingress in infra. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires routing requests to blog.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blog.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: gateway-ingress
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: log-aggregator
spec:
  rules:
  - host: blog.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: frontend-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,4
830,The ssl-terminator-config ConfigMap operates in the production namespace. It has where the log_level field is info. It includes storing rate_limit with value 100. It includes feature_flags configured as beta=true. It has which includes a feature_flags key. It includes where log_level contains inf.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""inf""}, {""path"": ""data.rate_limit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100""}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta=true""}, {""path"": ""data.log_level"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""info""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-config
  namespace: production
data:
  feature_flags: beta=true
  rate_limit: '100'
  log_level: info
  timeout_seconds: '5'
  allowed_origins: '*'
  app_port: '8080'",ConfigMap,8
831,"We need a CronJob named payment-gateway-cron in ml. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. The configuration requires preserving the last 1 failed runs, additionally running a command starting with /bin/sh, scheduled at 0 3 * * 1-5, and also with concurrency policy Forbid, and with the container labeled task.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 3 * * 1-5""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.concurrencyPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Forbid""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: payment-gateway-cron
  namespace: ml
spec:
  schedule: 0 3 * * 1-5
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: prom/prometheus:4.0
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 500m
                memory: 512Mi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  suspend: false
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,8
832,Please configure a CronJob identified as data-pipeline-cron within staging. Make sure it has running on schedule 0 0 * * 1.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 1""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-cron
  namespace: staging
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 1
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: nginx:20
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 500m
                memory: 64Mi
          restartPolicy: Never
  suspend: false",CronJob,4
833,"Set up a Deployment called dns-resolver in the monitoring namespace. It should have a CPU request of 100m, with its container called dns-resolver, based on the kibana:14 image, and also running 2 copies, exposing container port 9200.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""9200""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""100m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
    env: testing
    tier: backend
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: dns-resolver
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: dns-resolver
        env: testing
        tier: backend
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: dns-resolver
        image: kibana:14
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9200
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 64Mi
        env:
        - name: NODE_ENV
          value: 'false'",Deployment,8
834,"We need a Pod named search-engine-pod in platform. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The configuration requires consul:stable as the base image, allocated 256Mi memory.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.memory"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""256Mi""}]","apiVersion: v1
