          value: 'true'",Deployment,6
854,We need an Ingress named email-sender-ingress in default. The configuration requires responding to requests for status.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""status.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: email-sender-ingress
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    rewrite-target: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: status.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /metrics
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: pdf-generator-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - status.example.com
    secretName: email-sender-tls",Ingress,4
855,The queue-worker-config ConfigMap operates in the staging namespace. It requires mapping timeout_seconds to 10. It is configured with having debug_mode=false in its data. It includes including a debug_mode data key. It has where feature_flags contains bet. It requires a timeout_seconds entry present.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.feature_flags"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""bet""}, {""path"": ""data.timeout_seconds"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.timeout_seconds"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""data.debug_mode"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: queue-worker-config
  namespace: staging
data:
  timeout_seconds: '10'
  debug_mode: 'false'
  feature_flags: beta=true",ConfigMap,8
856,"Provision an Ingress called proxy-server-ingress in the platform namespace. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It should have pathType Exact, serving beta.example.com, and with TLS enabled for host beta.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: proxy-server-ingress
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: beta.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: stream-consumer-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - beta.example.com
    secretName: proxy-server-tls",Ingress,6
857,"We need a Deployment named user-service in default. The configuration requires the version label set to v2, using envoyproxy/envoy:8 as its container image, whose container is called app, with 10 replicas.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""envoyproxy/envoy:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.version"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: user-service
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: user-service
    tier: database
    env: production
    version: v2
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: user-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: user-service
        tier: database
        env: production
        version: v2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: envoyproxy/envoy:8
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 64Mi",Deployment,7
858,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name config-server, deployed to development. Specifications include with 4 replicas, while also allocated 1000m CPU, naming the container main, and built from debian:5.0.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:5.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1000m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: config-server
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: config-server
    version: v1.0
    team: infra
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: config-server
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: config-server
        version: v1.0
        team: infra
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: debian:5.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 4Gi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,7
859,"Please configure a Deployment identified as web-app within ml. Documentation for this component is maintained in the team wiki under infrastructure/configs. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Make sure it has the container identified as app, needing 500m of CPU, with 1 replicas, using centos:2.0 as its container image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-app
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: web-app
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web-app
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web-app
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: centos:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 4Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,7
860,The circuit-breaker Deployment operates in the infra namespace. It is configured with running 5 copies. It features based on the bitnami/kafka:slim image. It requires running in a container named server. It requires labeled release=blue.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""circuit-breaker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:slim""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.release"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blue""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: circuit-breaker
    version: v2.1
    release: blue
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: circuit-breaker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: circuit-breaker
        version: v2.1
        release: blue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: bitnami/kafka:slim
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: '8080'",Deployment,7
861,"We need a Deployment named health-checker in default. The configuration requires whose container is called server, scaled to 4 instances, additionally running debian:3.1.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""debian:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
