        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: order-service-svc
            port:
              number: 443",Ingress,7
864,The service-mesh-cron CronJob operates in the ml namespace. It is configured with labeled env=production. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. It includes launching with the /bin/sh command prefix. It includes running in a container named task. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. It requires built from postgres:alpine. It is configured with scheduled at */30 * * * *.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/30 * * * *""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.command.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/bin/sh""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:alpine""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: service-mesh-cron
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    env: production
spec:
  schedule: '*/30 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: postgres:alpine
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - echo hello
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow",CronJob,8
865,The stream-consumer Deployment operates in the development namespace. It requires a CPU request of 1. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. It has scaled to 2 instances. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It has whose container is called main. It includes prom/prometheus:1.2 as its container image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""prom/prometheus:1.2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: stream-consumer
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: stream-consumer
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: stream-consumer
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: prom/prometheus:1.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 2Gi",Deployment,7
866,"Configure an Ingress called session-store-ingress in the ml namespace. It should have handling the /health endpoint, with a Prefix pathType, and responding to requests for admin.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""session-store-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""admin.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/health""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: session-store-ingress
  namespace: ml
  annotations:
    ssl-redirect: 50m
spec:
  rules:
  - host: admin.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /health
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: notification-svc-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  ingressClassName: istio",Ingress,6
867,"The metrics-collector-pod Pod operates in the staging namespace. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. It has postgres:20 as its container image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:20""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: metrics-collector-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
    env: staging
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: postgres:20
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 750m
        memory: 4Gi",Pod,4
868,"Please configure a Service identified as cdn-origin-svc within ml. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. Make sure it has forwarding to target port 8200, and also with service type NodePort, and also using TCP protocol, and selecting pods labeled app=order-service.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8200""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TCP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: order-service
  ports:
  - port: 5000
    targetPort: 8200
    protocol: TCP",Service,7
869,"Deploy a Deployment called analytics-engine in the ml namespace. It should have scaled to 1 instances, and also built from kibana:11, additionally configured with Never pull behavior, the container identified as app.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""analytics-engine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""kibana:11""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: analytics-engine
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: analytics-engine
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: analytics-engine
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: analytics-engine
