        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        imagePullPolicy: Never",Deployment,7
870,The health-checker-svc Service operates in the ml namespace. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. It is configured with labeled team=ml. It has configured as LoadBalancer.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: health-checker-svc
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: health-checker
    team: ml
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: session-store
  ports:
  - port: 9090
    targetPort: 8080
    protocol: TCP",Service,5
871,The api-server-cron CronJob operates in the development namespace. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. Feature flags controlling this service are managed through LaunchDarkly. It has running on schedule 0 0 * * 0. It features OnFailure restart behavior.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 0""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: api-server-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 0
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: alpine:latest
            command:
            - curl
            - -s
            - http://api/health
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,5
872,"Please configure an Ingress identified as webhook-relay-ingress within infra. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. Make sure it has a Prefix pathType, using ingress class nginx, serving ws.example.com, enabling TLS on ws.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""webhook-relay-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ws.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Prefix""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ws.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.ingressClassName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nginx""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: webhook-relay-ingress
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    env: testing
spec:
  rules:
  - host: ws.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api/v2
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - ws.example.com
    secretName: webhook-relay-tls
  ingressClassName: nginx",Ingress,7
873,"Set up a Deployment called api-server in the ml namespace. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. It should have httpd:17 as its container image, while also tagged as release=blue, with a replica count of 8, the container identified as worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:17""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.release"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""blue""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: api-server
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: api-server
    env: testing
    release: blue
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: api-server
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: api-server
        env: testing
        release: blue
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: httpd:17
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9000",Deployment,7
874,The load-balancer-config ConfigMap operates in the logging namespace. It has including a timeout_seconds data key.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""load-balancer-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""data.timeout_seconds"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}]","apiVersion: v1
