  name: backend-config
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
data:
  cache_ttl: '600'
  timeout_seconds: '10'",ConfigMap,4
951,The health-checker-pod Pod operates in the platform namespace. It includes running in a container named app. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It includes a restart policy of Always. The on-call rotation for this service follows the standard PagerDuty schedule. It is configured with running centos:8.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""centos:8""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: health-checker-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: health-checker
    tier: frontend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: centos:8
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,6
952,"We need a CronJob named report-gen-cron in monitoring. Ensure this configuration is reviewed by the security team before deployment. The configuration requires bearing the label app=worker, with the cron schedule 0 */6 * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 */6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: report-gen-cron
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: worker
spec:
  schedule: 0 */6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: runner
            image: golang:3.9
          restartPolicy: Never
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,5
953,The backend-ingress Ingress operates in the data namespace. It features bound to host v2.api.example.com. It has TLS termination using secret backend-tls.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.api.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: backend-ingress
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: proxy-server
spec:
  rules:
  - host: v2.api.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /static
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: api-server-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - v2.api.example.com
    secretName: backend-tls",Ingress,5
954,"Provision a Deployment called search-engine in the default namespace. It should have a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, using grafana/grafana:20 as its container image, running in a container named server, while also with the version label set to v2.0, and running 8 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""search-engine""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""grafana/grafana:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.version"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""v2.0""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: search-engine
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: search-engine
    version: v2.0
    tier: backend
spec:
  replicas: 8
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: search-engine
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: search-engine
        version: v2.0
        tier: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: grafana/grafana:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9092",Deployment,8
955,The gateway-cron CronJob operates in the infra namespace. It requires preserving the last 2 failed runs. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. It includes labeled team=data. It has running httpd:1.0. It has set to fire at 0 0 * * 0.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 0 * * 0""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:1.0""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.failedJobsHistoryLimit"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: gateway-cron
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    team: data
spec:
  schedule: 0 0 * * 0
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: httpd:1.0
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 200m
                memory: 4Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,7
956,"Create a Deployment called cron-runner in the production namespace. It should have scaled to 3 instances, the container should share the same name as the resource itself, additionally built from busybox:14.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""busybox:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cron-runner
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
    version: v3.0
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cron-runner
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cron-runner
        version: v3.0
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: cron-runner
        image: busybox:14
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 128Mi
        imagePullPolicy: Always",Deployment,6
957,"Provision a Pod called dns-resolver-pod in the monitoring namespace. It should have carrying the app=dns-resolver label, configuring the METRICS_PORT variable, with prom/prometheus:stable as the base image, and naming the container server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""prom/prometheus:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""METRICS_PORT""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""dns-resolver""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: dns-resolver-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: dns-resolver
    team: ml
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: prom/prometheus:stable
    ports:
    - containerPort: 6379
    env:
    - name: METRICS_PORT
      value: debug
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Pod,7
958,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name queue-worker-config, deployed to staging. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. Specifications include with timeout_seconds configured as 10, and mapping cache_ttl to 60.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""data.cache_ttl"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""60""}, {""path"": ""data.timeout_seconds"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: queue-worker-config
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: catalog-api
data:
  workers: '4'
  cache_ttl: '60'
  app_env: production
  timeout_seconds: '10'
  redis_host: redis://redis-master:6379",ConfigMap,5
959,"We need a Pod named api-server-pod in monitoring. The configuration requires memcached:3.1 as the base image, additionally reserving 2 CPU resources, with Never restart behavior.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""memcached:3.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Never""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: api-server-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: api-server
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: memcached:3.1
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '2'
