    ports:
    - containerPort: 9090",Pod,6
964,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name data-pipeline-svc, deployed to platform. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Specifications include selecting pods labeled app=analytics-engine, operating as a LoadBalancer service, additionally serving on port 11211.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""analytics-engine""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""11211""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline-svc
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    team: data
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: analytics-engine
  ports:
  - port: 11211
    targetPort: 4222
    protocol: UDP",Service,6
965,The cdn-origin Deployment operates in the development namespace. It includes scaled to 5 instances. It features built from python:4.0. It has the container labeled cdn-origin.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn-origin""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: cdn-origin
  namespace: development
  labels:
    app: cdn-origin
    tier: cache
    version: v2.0
    release: canary
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: cdn-origin
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: cdn-origin
        tier: cache
        version: v2.0
        release: canary
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: cdn-origin
        image: python:4.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        env:
        - name: NODE_ENV
          value: 'true'",Deployment,6
966,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a CronJob with name ssl-terminator-cron, deployed to development. Specifications include with the cron schedule 0 */6 * * *, and with the container labeled worker.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ssl-terminator-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 */6 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: ssl-terminator-cron
  namespace: development
spec:
  schedule: 0 */6 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: centos:17
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 100m
                memory: 1Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  suspend: false",CronJob,5
967,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name cache-proxy-pod, deployed to infra. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. Specifications include pulling golang:4.0, with OnFailure restart behavior, and also naming the container app, bearing the app label cache-proxy, and pulling images with policy IfNotPresent.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:4.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""IfNotPresent""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: cache-proxy-pod
  namespace: infra
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: golang:4.0
    env:
    - name: WORKERS
      value: 'false'
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Pod,8
968,The inventory-svc-pod Pod operates in the staging namespace. It includes openjdk:3.9 as the base image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:3.9""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc-pod
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: openjdk:3.9
    ports:
    - containerPort: 3306
    env:
    - name: SECRET_KEY
      value: '8080'
    imagePullPolicy: Never",Pod,4
969,"We need a Deployment named event-bus in logging. Related services include the auth-proxy and rate-limiter deployments in the same namespace. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The configuration requires nats:1.1 as the base image, with a RollingUpdate rollout strategy, and also scaled to 4 instances, and also with its container called event-bus, and limited to 1 CPU.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""4""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""nats:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: event-bus
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: event-bus
spec:
  replicas: 4
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: event-bus
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: event-bus
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: event-bus
        image: nats:1.1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 443
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 256Mi
          limits:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 256Mi",Deployment,8
970,"Deploy a Pod called service-mesh-pod in the monitoring namespace. It should have service account app-sa, additionally whose container is called runner, and running alpine:17.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""service-mesh-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:17""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""runner""}, {""path"": ""spec.serviceAccountName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app-sa""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: service-mesh-pod
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: service-mesh
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: alpine:17
  serviceAccountName: app-sa",Pod,6
971,We need an Ingress named user-service-ingress in production. The configuration requires routing requests to example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""example.com""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: user-service-ingress
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: order-service
spec:
  rules:
  - host: example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: scheduler-svc
            port:
              number: 3000",Ingress,4
972,Please configure a Pod identified as catalog-api-pod within data. Make sure it has based on the ubuntu:8 image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""catalog-api-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ubuntu:8""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: catalog-api-pod
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: catalog-api
    env: staging
spec:
  restartPolicy: Never
  containers:
  - name: server
    image: ubuntu:8",Pod,4
973,The notification-svc Deployment operates in the data namespace. It features deployed via Recreate. It is configured with whose container is called notification-svc. It has 2 replicas. It has node:3.9 as the base image. It features container port 3306.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""node:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3306""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: notification-svc
  namespace: data
  labels:
    app: notification-svc
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: notification-svc
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: notification-svc
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: notification-svc
        image: node:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 1Gi",Deployment,8
974,We need a Service named backend-svc in ml. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. The configuration requires configured as NodePort.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""backend-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: backend-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: log-aggregator
  ports:
  - port: 27017
    targetPort: 15672
    protocol: TCP
  sessionAffinity: ClientIP",Service,4
975,"We need a Deployment named order-service in staging. The configuration requires 10 replicas, whose container is called server, and also serving on container port 6379, based on the minio/minio:2.0 image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""minio/minio:2.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: order-service
  namespace: staging
  labels:
    app: order-service
    version: v1
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: order-service
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: order-service
        version: v1
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: minio/minio:2.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 256Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        env:
        - name: API_KEY
          value: production",Deployment,7
976,"Spin up a CronJob called audit-logger-cron in the default namespace. It should have whose container is called task, and executing on the 0 */2 * * * cron schedule.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""audit-logger-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""0 */2 * * *""}, {""path"": ""spec.jobTemplate.spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""task""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: audit-logger-cron
  namespace: default
  labels:
    team: ml
spec:
  schedule: 0 */2 * * *
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: task
            image: minio/minio:21
            resources:
              requests:
                cpu: 100m
                memory: 4Gi
          restartPolicy: Never
  concurrencyPolicy: Allow
  failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2",CronJob,5
977,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name order-service-pod, deployed to production. This component is part of the Q3 platform migration project. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. Specifications include with a restart policy of OnFailure, while also tagged with app: order-service, additionally declaring the DEBUG env var, with httpd:1.1 as the base image, needing 500m of CPU.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:1.1""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""500m""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""DEBUG""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: order-service-pod
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: order-service
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: worker
    image: httpd:1.1
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: 500m
        memory: 128Mi
    env:
    - name: DEBUG
      value: 'false'",Pod,8
978,The event-bus-ingress Ingress operates in the production namespace. It requires carrying label app: cache-proxy. It includes serving on port 8080. It is configured with directing traffic for the host cdn.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.port.number"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: event-bus-ingress
  namespace: production
  annotations:
    description: 'true'
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
spec:
  rules:
  - host: cdn.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /docs
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: load-balancer-svc
            port:
              number: 8080",Ingress,6
979,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name batch-processor-pod, deployed to ml. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana. Specifications include restart mode set to OnFailure, additionally pulling golang:1.0, and also with env var TIMEOUT assigned to false, and with the app label set to batch-processor.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""golang:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""false""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-pod
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    team: platform
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: runner
    image: golang:1.0
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: 'false'
    imagePullPolicy: Never
  serviceAccountName: default",Pod,7
980,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name file-uploader-svc, deployed to ml. Specifications include as a LoadBalancer service, listening on port 3306.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3306""}]","apiVersion: v1
