983,"We need a CronJob named file-uploader-cron in default. Expected traffic volume is approximately 10,000 requests per second during peak hours. The configuration requires running on schedule */5 * * * *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""CronJob""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""file-uploader-cron""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.schedule"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*/5 * * * *""}]","apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: file-uploader-cron
  namespace: default
  labels:
    team: data
spec:
  schedule: '*/5 * * * *'
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: worker
            image: busybox:14
            command:
            - python
            - run_job.py
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
  successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1",CronJob,4
984,"Configure a Service called report-gen-svc in the ml namespace. It should have operating as a NodePort service, while also via UDP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""report-gen-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: report-gen-svc
  namespace: ml
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: service-mesh
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 9092
    protocol: UDP",Service,5
985,"Please configure a Service identified as user-service-svc within monitoring. Make sure it has targeting pods with app=config-server, forwarding to target port 443, set up as NodePort, and communicating over UDP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""user-service-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""config-server""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""443""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: user-service-svc
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: config-server
  ports:
  - port: 8500
    targetPort: 443
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 31631",Service,7
986,"We need a Pod named event-bus-pod in platform. The configuration requires the DEBUG environment variable, the container identified as main, and also where DEBUG equals 8080, with a restart policy of OnFailure, using consul:stable as its container image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""consul:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""8080""}, {""path"": ""spec.restartPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""OnFailure""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""DEBUG""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: event-bus-pod
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: event-bus
spec:
  restartPolicy: OnFailure
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: consul:stable
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    env:
    - name: DEBUG
      value: '8080'",Pod,8
987,Spin up a ConfigMap called web-app-config in the production namespace. This configuration supersedes the legacy setup that was decommissioned last quarter. The associated monitoring dashboard is available on Grafana.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: web-app-config
  namespace: production
data:
  retry_count: '10'
  api_key_prefix: sk-
  app_name: search-engine",ConfigMap,3
988,"Create a Deployment called event-bus in the platform namespace. It should have the container identified as worker, employing RollingUpdate for deployments, pulling bitnami/kafka:3.9, running 6 copies.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""event-bus""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:3.9""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""RollingUpdate""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: event-bus
  namespace: platform
  labels:
    app: event-bus
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: event-bus
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: event-bus
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: bitnami/kafka:3.9
        ports:
        - containerPort: 11211
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 750m
            memory: 2Gi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 2Gi
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent",Deployment,7
989,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a ConfigMap with name stream-consumer-config, deployed to infra. Specifications include where the app_name entry includes rep, additionally which includes a allowed_origins key, and also including a app_name data key, storing allowed_origins with value *.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ConfigMap""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""stream-consumer-config""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""infra""}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""exists"", ""value"": """"}, {""path"": ""data.app_name"", ""operator"": ""contains"", ""value"": ""rep""}, {""path"": ""data.allowed_origins"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""*""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: stream-consumer-config
  namespace: infra
data:
  allowed_origins: '*'
  app_name: report-gen",ConfigMap,7
990,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: an Ingress with name order-service-ingress, deployed to monitoring. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Specifications include enabling TLS on beta.example.com, carrying annotation description: 50m, with the app label set to metrics-collector, bound to host beta.example.com.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""metrics-collector""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""beta.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.annotations.description"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""50m""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: order-service-ingress
  namespace: monitoring
  annotations:
    description: 50m
  labels:
    app: metrics-collector
spec:
  rules:
  - host: beta.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
        backend:
          service:
            name: notification-svc-svc
            port:
              number: 443
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - beta.example.com
    secretName: order-service-tls",Ingress,7
991,The api-server-svc Service operates in the logging namespace. It has accessible at node port 32000. It has set up as NodePort. It is configured with target port set to 1883. It has exposing port 15672. It includes the team label set to frontend.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""api-server-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.team"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""frontend""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""15672""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.nodePort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""32000""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: api-server-svc
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: api-server
    team: frontend
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: cron-runner
  ports:
  - port: 15672
    targetPort: 1883
    protocol: UDP
    nodePort: 32000",Service,8
992,"We need a Deployment named inventory-svc in production. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. The configuration requires scaled to 3 instances, based on the alpine:14 image, additionally with env var DEBUG assigned to info, and with its container called server.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""inventory-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""alpine:14""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""server""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.env.0.value"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""info""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: inventory-svc
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: inventory-svc
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: inventory-svc
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: inventory-svc
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: server
        image: alpine:14
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8500
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 128Mi
        env:
        - name: DEBUG
          value: info",Deployment,7
993,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Pod with name web-app-pod, deployed to logging. Specifications include based on the bitnami/kafka:alpine image, with its container called app, and tagged as env=development.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""logging""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""bitnami/kafka:alpine""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""development""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: web-app-pod
  namespace: logging
  labels:
    app: web-app
    env: development
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: bitnami/kafka:alpine
    ports:
    - containerPort: 3000",Pod,6
994,The batch-processor-svc Service operates in the default namespace. It includes exposing port 6379. It features routing to pods where app is image-processor. It is configured with target port set to 5432. It is configured with operating as a ClusterIP service. Performance benchmarks show this configuration handles 500 concurrent connections comfortably. It features carrying label env: testing.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""batch-processor-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClusterIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6379""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.targetPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""5432""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.env"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""testing""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""image-processor""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: batch-processor-svc
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: batch-processor
    env: testing
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: image-processor
  ports:
  - port: 6379
    targetPort: 5432
    protocol: UDP",Service,8
995,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Deployment with name web-app, deployed to monitoring. Specifications include with a replica count of 6, while also pulling openjdk:stable, whose container is called main.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""web-app""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""6""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""openjdk:stable""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-app
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: web-app
spec:
  replicas: 6
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web-app
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web-app
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: openjdk:stable
        ports:
        - containerPort: 27017
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '1'
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
        env:
        - name: MAX_RETRIES
          value: '3'",Deployment,6
996,The cache-proxy-svc Service operates in the ml namespace. It has operating on UDP. It is configured with port 1883 open. It has operating as a NodePort service.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""NodePort""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.port"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}, {""path"": ""spec.ports.0.protocol"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""UDP""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
