1060,The order-service-ingress Ingress operates in the ml namespace. It requires bound to host app.example.com. Cost allocation for this resource falls under the platform-infrastructure budget category. It has labeled app=cache-proxy. It requires TLS termination on app.example.com. It includes pathType Exact. It has forwarding requests to the model-trainer-svc service.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ml""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""model-trainer-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""app.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Exact""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cache-proxy""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: order-service-ingress
  namespace: ml
  labels:
    app: cache-proxy
spec:
  rules:
  - host: app.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /health
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: model-trainer-svc
            port:
              number: 3000
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - app.example.com
    secretName: order-service-tls",Ingress,8
1061,"We need a Deployment named proxy-server in production. The configuration requires scaled to 3 instances, using python:1.0 as its container image, and also limited to 250m CPU, and with its container called main.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""proxy-server""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""3""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""python:1.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""main""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.resources.limits.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""250m""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: proxy-server
  namespace: production
  labels:
    app: proxy-server
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: proxy-server
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: proxy-server
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: main
        image: python:1.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: '2'
            memory: 512Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 1Gi",Deployment,7
1062,"We need a Deployment named queue-worker in monitoring. The team responsible for this resource can be reached via the platform-ops Slack channel. This was previously hosted on AWS ECS before the Kubernetes migration. The configuration requires a Recreate rollout strategy, while also with 2 replicas, while also serving on container port 1883, running in a container named queue-worker, with postgres:20 as the base image.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""monitoring""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""2""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:20""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""queue-worker""}, {""path"": ""spec.strategy.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Recreate""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.ports.0.containerPort"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1883""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: queue-worker
  namespace: monitoring
  labels:
    app: queue-worker
    release: green
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: queue-worker
  strategy:
    type: Recreate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: queue-worker
        release: green
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: queue-worker
        image: postgres:20
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 256Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 256Mi
        env:
        - name: APP_NAME
          value: info",Deployment,8
1063,"Configure the following Kubernetes resource: a Service with name notification-svc-svc, deployed to platform. Rollback procedures for this deployment are documented in the runbook. The SLA for this service requires 99.95% uptime. Specifications include routing to pods where app is order-service, as a LoadBalancer service, with sticky sessions via ClientIP.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Service""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""notification-svc-svc""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.type"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""LoadBalancer""}, {""path"": ""spec.sessionAffinity"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ClientIP""}, {""path"": ""spec.selector.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""order-service""}]","apiVersion: v1
