1115,"We need an Ingress named health-checker-ingress in production. Capacity planning documents suggest this workload will double by end of year. Integration tests for this component run in the CI pipeline on every merge to main. The configuration requires TLS termination on staging.example.com, secured via TLS secret health-checker-tls, while also routing requests to staging.example.com, while also directing traffic to service email-sender-svc, annotated with app=cron-runner.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""production""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.backend.service.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""email-sender-svc""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.hosts.0"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""staging.example.com""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cron-runner""}, {""path"": ""spec.tls.0.secretName"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""health-checker-tls""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: health-checker-ingress
  namespace: production
  annotations:
    proxy-body-size: 50m
  labels:
    app: cron-runner
spec:
  rules:
  - host: staging.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /uploads
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: email-sender-svc
            port:
              number: 8080
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - staging.example.com
    secretName: health-checker-tls",Ingress,8
1116,"We need a Pod named gateway-pod in default. Note that this resource may be scaled horizontally during high-traffic events. The configuration requires reserving 1 CPU resources, based on the httpd:latest image, pulling images with policy Always, with the TIMEOUT environment variable, and labeled app=gateway.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""httpd:latest""}, {""path"": ""metadata.labels.app"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""gateway""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.env.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""TIMEOUT""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.resources.requests.cpu"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""1""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.imagePullPolicy"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Always""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: gateway-pod
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: gateway
    tier: backend
spec:
  restartPolicy: Always
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: httpd:latest
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: '1'
        memory: 64Mi
    env:
    - name: TIMEOUT
      value: 'true'
    imagePullPolicy: Always",Pod,8
1117,The payment-gateway-ingress Ingress operates in the default namespace. It is configured with routing /static requests. It includes path matching set to ImplementationSpecific. It has bound to host cdn.example.com.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""payment-gateway-ingress""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.host"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""cdn.example.com""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.pathType"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""ImplementationSpecific""}, {""path"": ""spec.rules.0.http.paths.0.path"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""/static""}]","apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
