          value: 'true'",Deployment,6
1148,"Configure a Deployment called data-pipeline in the default namespace. It should have pulling rabbitmq:3.0, with its container called worker, and maintaining 10 pods.","[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Deployment""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""default""}, {""path"": ""spec.replicas"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""10""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""rabbitmq:3.0""}, {""path"": ""spec.template.spec.containers.0.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""worker""}]","apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: data-pipeline
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: data-pipeline
    team: platform
    tier: backend
spec:
  replicas: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: data-pipeline
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: data-pipeline
        team: platform
        tier: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: worker
        image: rabbitmq:3.0
        ports:
        - containerPort: 1883
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
        - name: LOG_LEVEL
          value: '60'",Deployment,6
1149,Please configure a Pod identified as data-pipeline-pod within platform. Make sure it has based on the postgres:11 image.,"[{""path"": ""kind"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""Pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.name"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""data-pipeline-pod""}, {""path"": ""metadata.namespace"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""platform""}, {""path"": ""spec.containers.0.image"", ""operator"": ""equals"", ""value"": ""postgres:11""}]","apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
